Name: A Very Supernatural Christmas
Description: In this Christmas episode, Sam and Dean track an "anti-Santa" who abducts victims through chimneys. Dean wants to celebrate as they used to, but Sam faces the reality that it might be their last Christmas together.

Name: It's the Great Pumpkin, Sam Winchester
Description: Sam and Dean investigate mysterious deaths in a town and uncover a witch's plan to summon an ancient and dangerous demon.

Name: My Bloody Valentine
Description: Castiel assists Sam and Dean as they track down Cupid, who is responsible for a string of love-related killings on Valentine's Day.

Name: Love Hurts
Description: In this Valentine's Day-themed episode, Sam and Dean investigate a series of murders caused by an ancient curse that marks its victims for death.

Name: Last Holiday
Description: Dean and Sam find a wood nymph living in their bunker, who will do whatever it takes to protect her "family".

Name: The Man in the Fallout Shelter
Description: The gang investigates a skeleton found in a fallout shelter while quarantined in the lab for Christmas after Zack accidentally releases deadly fungus spores.

Name: Mummy in the Maze
Description: Booth and Bones investigate the discovery of two mummified girls and search for a missing girl while checking a fun house, Halloween maze, and church charity for leads.

Name: The Santa in the Slush
Description: Brennan and Booth investigate the death of a Santa while trying to make the holiday special for their loved ones: Bones attempts to fulfill her father's Christmas wishes, while Booth copes with not being with his son.

Name: The Goop on the Girl
Description: Brennan and Booth investigate a Santa Claus who blew himself up during a bank robbery. Meanwhile, Brennan plans to spend Christmas in El Salvador, but her father convinces her to stay with Margaret, a distant relative.

Name: High Treason in the Holiday Season
Description: A journalist investigating corruption is found dead. Hodgins becomes paranoid over the investigation being monitored. The team gathers for Thanksgiving.

Name: Lexmas
Description: On Christmas Eve, Lex is shot during a car-jacking and has to undergo surgery. While he's under, Lex dreams of an alternate future with Lana. Clark helps Chloe deliver Christmas presents to underprivileged children.

Name: Gemini
Description: Lois receives a call that Chloe is attached to a bomb. Chloe reveals her healing powers to Jimmy while trapped in an elevator. Clark returns from the Fortress of Solitude and wants to take down Lex with Lana's help.

Name: Damned if You Do
Description: House treats a nun for dermatitis and asthma but his diagnosis and treatment may have been wrong, leading to a life-threatening situation.

Name: Merry Little Christmas
Description: Wilson proposes a deal to House with Cuddy's support, while the team struggles with a difficult case and keeps seeking House's opinion despite his unavailability.

Name: Insensitive
Description: House interferes with relationships on Valentine's Day while trying to diagnose a teenage patient who cannot feel pain due to a genetic condition.

Name: It's a Wonderful Lie
Description: House becomes preoccupied with a mother and daughter who can't lie and uses Christmas to create tension among his team.

Name: Joy to the World
Description: A teen collapses on stage, leading to a surprise for Cuddy. Wilson persuades House to be kinder to patients during the holidays. Foreman and Thirteen have trouble with a trial patient dropping out.

Name: Ignorance is Bliss
Description: A high IQ courier collapses at a bookstore, while House continues his antics to gain Cuddy's attention. The situation escalates when Chase punches House.

Name: My Day Off
Description: On Thanksgiving, J.D. gets diagnosed with appendicitis at Sacred Heart. Dr. Cox wants to impress his former mentor, Dr. Benson. Elliot attempts to be a more empathetic doctor.

Name: My Own Personal Jesus
Description: On Christmas, only Turk is in a festive mood. Cox asks J.D. to film a friend's baby's birth, but things don't go as planned.

Name: My Best Moment
Description: J.D. speaks to a group of pre-med students but decides to talk about his best experiences as a doctor.

Name: The One Where Underdog Gets Away
Description: The group is locked out of Monica and Rachel's apartment, causing their Thanksgiving plans to go wrong.

Name: The One with the Candy Hearts
Description: On Valentine's Day, Ross coincidentally dines in the same restaurant as Carol and Susan. Joey arranges a date for Chandler with Janice, while the girls burn keepsakes from past relationships.

Name: The One with Phoebe’s Dad
Description: Phoebe locates her father but is uncertain about whether to meet him or not.

Name: The One Where Ross and Rachel… You Know
Description: Monica develops a crush on her parents' friend while catering for him. Ross and Rachel have their first date. Joey and Chandler are reluctant to give up their new TV and armchairs.

Name: The One with the Football
Description: Monica and Ross's childhood rivalry causes a delay in Thanksgiving dinner as the group plays a game of touch football.

Name: The One Where Rachel Quits
Description: Ross accidentally breaks a little girl's leg and helps her sell cookies, which triggers Monica's past obsession. Rachel resigns from her job at Central Perk. Joey's Christmas tree selling clashes with Phoebe's beliefs.

Name: The One Where Ross and Rachel Take a Break
Description: After a fight with Rachel, Ross finds comfort in another woman's arms at a party. Phoebe's date requires an interpreter to communicate.

Name: The One with Chandler in a Box
Description: Chandler lies in a wooden box for six hours to apologize to Joey. Monica gets ice in her eye and is treated by Richard's son. Rachel's gift-giving habit is exposed.

Name: The One with the Girl from Poughkeepsie
Description: Monica hires Joey to demonstrate her authority to the kitchen staff by firing him. Chandler's attempt to set Rachel up with a co-worker fails, and Ross can't decide between two girls.

Name: The One with All the Thanksgivings
Description: The group recalls and shares their worst Thanksgiving experiences with each other.

Name: The One with the Inappropriate Sister
Description: Ross causes chaos in Chandler and Joey's lives out of boredom. Rachel is uneasy about Danny's close bond with his sister. Phoebe faces difficulties while collecting donations for the needy during Christmas.

Name: The One Where Everybody Finds Out
Description: Phoebe and Rachel discover Monica and Chandler's secret relationship and try to make them confess.

Name: The One Where Ross Got High
Description: Ross discloses why Jack and Judy dislike Chandler. Rachel attempts to make dessert for the group. Joey and Ross try to skip Thanksgiving with Janine and her dancer friends.

Name: The One with the Routine
Description: Joey tries to kiss Janine on the set of "Dick Clark's New Year's Rockin' Eve," and Monica and Ross perform their high school dance routine. Rachel, Phoebe, and Chandler search for Monica's Christmas gifts.

Name: The One With Unagi
Description: Rachel and Phoebe enroll in self-defense classes. Chandler and Monica exchange homemade Valentine's Day gifts. Joey participates in medical research to earn money.

Name: The One Where Chandler Doesn't Like Dogs
Description: Ross struggles to name all 50 states during a game, Joey ruins Rachel's chances with Tag during Thanksgiving dinner, and Phoebe sneaks a dog into the apartment, making Chandler nervous.

Name: The One with the Holiday Armadillo
Description: Ross wants to introduce Ben to Hanukkah, and Phoebe must drive a wedge between Rachel and Joey to entice her to move back into their refurbished apartment.

Name: The One with the Rumor
Description: Monica invites an old school friend, Will, to Thanksgiving dinner, unaware that he has a grudge against Rachel.

Name: The One with Ross's Step Forward
Description: Ross's new girlfriend wants to send out Christmas cards featuring a photo of them together, but Ross isn't sure he's ready to take that step yet.

Name: The One With The Birthing Video
Description: Phoebe gives Joey a happy dog to cheer him up. Monica accidentally gives Chandler a graphic birthing video instead of a romantic movie. Ross's girlfriend discovers Rachel is living with him.

Name: The One with Rachel's Other Sister
Description: Rachel's sister visits on Thanksgiving, causing arguments.

Name: The One with Christmas in Tulsa
Description: Chandler is sent to Tulsa for Christmas by his company, leaving Monica worried about his fidelity with a former Miss Oklahoma runner-up. Chandler returns early and announces he quit his job.

Name: The One with the Late Thanksgiving
Description: Monica and Chandler agree to host Thanksgiving, but Joey, Ross, Rachel, and Phoebe arrive an hour late for dinner.

Name: The One with Phoebe's Wedding
Description: Phoebe and Mike's wedding preparations go awry as last-minute issues arise.

Name: Halloween
Description: At a Halloween party, the gang sports various costumes, but Kelly's revealing outfit stands out. David meets with Scott and Brandon loses his twin niece and nephew while trick-or-treating.

Name: A Walsh Family Christmas
Description: Steve discovers the truth about his biological parents, while Dylan visits his imprisoned father. Brenda's homeless guest brings joy to the house, and Brandon and Emily establish a new friendship.

Name: Baby Makes Five
Description: On St. Valentine's Day, Dylan plans a memorable evening for Brenda while Kelly and David work to repair their parents' relationship.

Name: The Kindness of Strangers
Description: On a rainy Thanksgiving, Brandon invites homeless man Jack Canner over, while Steve breaks the news of his expulsion to his mother during a TV shoot in Santa Barbara.

Name: It's a Totally Happening Life
Description: Mysterious angels intervene and prevent a bus and a truck from crashing. Meanwhile, Dylan is asked to play Santa Claus for a group of underprivileged children.

Name: Radar Love
Description: Brandon reunites with Emily in San Francisco for Thanksgiving. Dylan agrees to dine with the Walshes, but Kelly causes a scene. Andrea is hesitant to attend Dan's parents' party but gives Jesse her address.

Name: Somewhere in the World It's Christmas
Description: The Walsh family's Hawaiian trip gets disrupted due to a plane malfunction. Dylan receives a surprise visit from a woman who claims to be Jack McKay's mistress with her daughter.

Name: Things That Go Bang in the Night
Description: Donna is spooked when her two love interests, Ray and Griffin, meet at a Halloween party. Valerie considers leaving town but stays after learning of her mother's breakdown.

Name: Christmas Comes This Time Each Year
Description: Felice tests Ray's love for Donna by offering him money; LuAnn goes Christmas shopping with Donna. Jesse and Andrea's differing family traditions cause tension. David meets Clare's father at a Christmas party.

Name: You Gotta Have Heart
Description: Steve tries to book "Jade" for a Valentine's Day telethon at the Peach Pit After Dark. Brandon temporarily distracts Kelly from her work. Valerie moves out and pressures Ray into an affair, while his mother covers for him.

Name: Breast Side Up
Description: Donna invites NFL quarterback over for Thanksgiving, but learns that she and Joe disapprove of premarital sex. Brandon and Kelly's old feelings return as they miss Susan and Colin. Steve becomes a hit at Clare's father's party.

Name: Angels We Have Heard on High
Description: Cindy returns to Beverly Hills for Christmas without Jim, while Colin's drug use puts a strain on his relationship with Kelly. Joe gives Donna a talking parrot for her birthday. Steve loses his job due to someone else's mistake.

Name: Turn Back the Clock
Description: The gang shares New Year's stories, including Steve babysitting his rowdy stepbrothers at the After Dark. Kelly and Colin's relationship is strained by his drug use, and Jonathan Casten's arrival causes problems between Susan and Brandon.

Name: Bleeding Hearts
Description: Clare bets Steve he won't stay celibate at a Valentine's Day party. Valerie's plan to keep David away from Ginger fails, causing David to leave her. Kelly hits rock bottom after getting beaten up while buying cocaine. Joe is kicked off the football team.

Name: Fearless
Description: Steve tries to make Clare jealous by dating someone else, while Donna's new boyfriend, Cliff, helps her with a Halloween party. Valerie resorts to her devious ways to avoid Kenny, and Kelly and Brandon have their own romantic pursuits.

Name: Gift Wrapped
Description: Valerie and Kelly exchange Christmas gifts, with Kelly discovering a surprise half-sister, Joy. Steve and Clare play matchmaker for their parents. David tries to impress Donna's conservative mother. Brandon and Tracy exchange gifts.

Name: My Funny Valentine
Description: Donna's ex-boyfriend causes trouble, while Valerie's mother visits and asks for money. Steve smokes pot with a guy he dislikes. David and Chloe perform at a Valentine's Day party. Kelly continues dating Tom, and Valerie tries to stop it.

Name: Santa Knows
Description: Kelly is asked to give a speech praising a questionable doctor, while Donna tries to get Noah in the holiday spirit and Steve sets out to prove Santa Claus is real with Nat's help.

Name: Cupid's Arrow
Description: Kelly goes on a Valentine's date with Jeff. Noah's half-brother tries to seduce Valerie with a date rape drug. David and Donna feel guilty about spending time together and get into a car accident

Name: You Say Goodbye, I Say Hello
Description: Donna's cousin, Gina, lies about her ice-skating career. Steve regrets his fling with Janet. Noah fears he caused a hit-and-run while driving drunk. David has a one-night stand with an underage listener. Valerie's behavior makes her leave for Buffalo.

Name: Beheading St. Valentine
Description: As Valentine's Day nears, Kelly feels uneasy around Matt after he reveals his wife's past. Steve's idea for a newspaper article on bikini models leads to a health scare, and Gina causes trouble between Donna and Noah.

Name: What's in a Name
Description: Janet gives birth prematurely while on her honeymoon. Dylan enlists Kelly and Nat to help with a Thanksgiving dinner at a community center. Donna discovers a past indiscretion by her father with Gina's mother.

Name: Nine Yolks Whipped Lightly
Description: Gina meets her biological father, but the meeting is awkward. Donna struggles to let go of Noah's past, while Dylan punches a neighbor during a community center Christmas gathering. Matt buys Kelly an engagement ring and proposes.

Name: The Final Proof
Description: Shane and his friend kidnap Noah and send a ransom email to Dylan. Kelly and Matt prepare for a game show, Donna goes with Matt when Kelly has nerves, and David's relationship with Camille is threatened by her ex.

Name: Thanks for the Memories
Description: On Thanksgiving, Meredith heads to the hospital, George joins his family for a hunting trip, and Izzie hosts a dinner party that no one seems to attend.

Name: Grandma Got Run Over By a Reindeer
Description: Izzie takes care of a man who fell off his roof while decorating for Christmas, while Cristina participates in a heart transplant surgery for a depressed boy. George deals with a difficult family during the holiday season.

Name: Haunt You Every Day
Description: Meredith becomes convinced that her mother's ashes are haunting her, while Cristina is unexpectedly denied a surgery.

Name: Holidaze
Description: Miranda's father disapproves of her life choices during the holiday season. Mark and Lexie are taken aback by the arrival of a woman from his past. Thatcher Grey questions the Chief's recent behavior, and Meredith defends him.

Name: Valentine's Day Massacre
Description: On Valentine's Day, the doctors deal with a collapsed restaurant roof and its aftermath. Derek juggles his Chief of Surgery duties, Meredith navigates her new role as Chief's wife, and Mark and Callie urge Sloane to make a decision about her baby.

Name: Adrift and at Peace
Description: Derek takes Cristina on a fishing trip despite Meredith's objections, while Teddy focuses on helping a dying patient with no insurance.

Name: All You Need Is Love
Description: Meredith and Derek get a Valentine's Day break with Lexie watching Zola; Callie has Mark babysit so she can surprise Arizona, and Bailey is impressed with Ben. The ER is filled with romantic emergencies.

Name: Thriller
Description: Costumed patients pose a challenge for doctors. Derek and Ben develop a new surgical technique. Richard angers Bailey by asking a resident to perform his next surgery.

Name: Girlfriend in a Coma
Description: Meredith learns more about her dating life from a patient, while Betty discloses information about Owen and Amelia.

Name: Whistlin' Past the Graveyard
Description: Alex tries to impress investors but is distracted by disturbing news of skeletons on the construction site. Teddy creates Halloween costumes for her children, and Meredith worries about missing trick-or-treating.

Name: Every Day Is a Holiday (With You)
Description: Meredith faces travel issues on Thanksgiving, while Amelia and Link reignite their relationship.

Name: It Came Upon a Midnight Clear
Description: Doctors celebrate the holidays and Meredith and Hamilton prepare for a project milestone, while Link wants to spend time with Amelia and their family. Schmitt faces a tough decision in surgery.

Name: Haunted
Description: On Halloween night at Grey Sloan Memorial, Meredith and Nick attempt to have some alone time, Levi becomes overwhelmed with work, and Winston and Owen have the interns practice trauma training on a cadaver.

Name: The Slutty Pumpkin
Description: Marshall and Lily attend a Halloween costume party, while Robin introduces her new boyfriend. Meanwhile, Ted and Barney go to their annual Halloween party, where Ted searches for his lost love, the Slutty Pumpkin.

Name: Belly Full of Turkey
Description: Marshall's Thanksgiving with his family becomes tense when Lily suspects she might be pregnant. Meanwhile, Robin, Barney, and Ted spend the holiday volunteering.

Name: The Limo
Description: Ted rents a limo for New Year's Eve 2005 and plans a night of celebration with the gang, but things don't go as expected.

Name: How Lily Stole Christmas
Description: Lily takes down her Christmas display after Ted insults her during her breakup with Marshall, and Barney falls ill.

Name: Slapsgiving
Description: Marshall prepares to deliver the third slap to Barney on Thanksgiving while Ted and Robin hook up the night before the holiday.

Name: Little Minnesota
Description: Ted tries to keep his sister from hooking up with Barney while she's visiting New York, and Robin hides her Canadian identity from Marshall and his Minnesota friends.

Name: Slapsgiving 2: Revenge of the Slap
Description: Barney becomes anxious when Marshall gives Ted and Robin the power to slap him as part of a bet. Lily's father unexpectedly arrives for Thanksgiving dinner and Robin starts frequenting a Minnesota-themed bar.

Name: Blitzgiving
Description: Ted plans a Thanksgiving dinner for his friends, but leaves early and misses out on all the fun with an old college friend nicknamed The Blitz. The rest of the gang has a wild night, leaving Ted to spend Thanksgiving with Zoey instead.

Name: False Positive
Description: Barney and Robin consider making significant life changes after learning that Lily is pregnant. However, they change their minds when Marshall and Lily reveal that it was a false alarm.

Name: Desperation Day
Description: Lily heads to Minnesota to convince Marshall to come back, but he's not ready to leave. Meanwhile, Ted and Zoey's relationship faces challenges, and Barney tries to find a date for Valentine's Day.

Name: The Slutty Pumpkin Returns
Description: Ted reconnects with his long-lost crush from a Halloween party, while Lily's "pregnancy brain" convinces her to move to the suburbs. Barney discovers he's one-quarter Canadian.

Name: The Rebound Girl
Description: Robin opposes Marshall and Lily's plan to move to Long Island, while Ted and Barney decide to become "bro-parents."

Name: Symphony of Illumination
Description: Barney and Robin receive unexpected news after Robin tells Barney she's pregnant. Meanwhile, Marshall is pranked by a teenager while decorating for Christmas.

Name: The Final Page: Part One
Description: Ted wants to show off his new building to an old professor, Barney is stuck in a jinx, and Marshall and Lily bump into an irritating old friend. Robin is offered a chance to fire Patrice.

Name: The Final Page: Part Two
Description: Ted is torn between keeping a promise to Barney and telling Robin about his proposal plans, and taking her as his date to the opening of his new building. Meanwhile, Marshall and Lily look forward to a rare night out.

Name: The Red Dot
Description: George works at Elaine's office and starts dating the cleaning woman. Jerry's carelessness causes Elaine's alcoholic boyfriend to relapse, and George buys Elaine a discounted cashmere sweater.

Name: The Pick
Description: George breaks up with Susan but then wants her back, only to break up with her again. Elaine takes a revealing photo for her Christmas cards. Jerry's girlfriend sees him picking his nose and breaks up with him.

Name: The Mom and Pop Store
Description: George buys a convertible and believes it belonged to Jon Voight. Kramer helps a struggling shoe-repair business. Elaine wins a radio quiz to help Mr. Pitt be in the Macy's Thanksgiving Day Parade.

Name: The Strike
Description: Jerry dates a woman whose appearance drastically changes every day. Kramer returns to work at H&H Bagels. George creates a fake charity. Elaine gives a guy a fake phone number.

Name: Merry Thanksgiving
Description: Charlie tries to host a traditional Thanksgiving dinner, but has to bribe his family members to attend. The usual family conflicts arise and tensions escalate. Judith's parents disapprove of their daughter's relationship with a woman.

Name: Hi, Mr. Horned One
Description: Charlie's girlfriend, who is a Satan-worshiper, has a talent for the supernatural, and some strange occurrences are taking place around the Harper household.

Name: Santa's Village of the Damned
Description: Alan's girlfriend Sandy is a great cook and homemaker, which leads to Charlie and Alan gaining weight from her delicious meals. However, her increasingly erratic behavior becomes too much for them to handle.

Name: Walnuts and Demerol
Description: Charlie's attempts to have a one-night stand on Christmas Eve are jeopardized when his family and friends unexpectedly show up at his house and refuse to leave.

Name: I'd Like to Start with the Cat
Description: Charlie's careless words and inattention to details result in him and his girlfriend being sent to couples counseling.

Name: Warning, It's Dirty
Description: Charlie goes against Alan's wishes and urges Jake to pursue a girl he met on the beach, while his girlfriend is away for Christmas.

Name: One False Move, Zimbabwe!
Description: During Christmas, Walden's mother comes to visit and Alan develops a crush on her. However, she reveals a dark secret about Walden's past involving a pet, which sends him into an emotional breakdown.

Name: Sips, Sonnets and Sodomy
Description: Alan and Walden's Valentine's Day plans are ruined when a heavy storm traps them at home with their bickering girlfriends.

Name: Give Santa a Tail-Hole
Description: Walden poses as a Christmas tree salesman and unexpectedly receives a business proposal from Mark Zuckerberg. Meanwhile, Alan is left alone at the beach house during the holiday season.

Name: Advantage: Fat, Flying Baby
Description: Walden hopes for a Valentine's date with Kate but she only wants to be friends. Alan tries to impress Lyndsey but ends up in the hospital. Rose lures Kate to China for a business deal.

Name: On Vodka, on Soda, on Blender, on Mixer!
Description: Walden aids Jenny in securing a second date with a woman who is avoiding her, while Alan is propositioned by his girlfriend's ex-partner.

Name: The Ol' Mexican Spinach
Description: On Halloween, Walden faces a health scare that prompts him to reassess his priorities with Alan's support.

Name: Family, Buble, Deep-Fried Turkey
Description: Walden tries to restore Louis' Christmas spirit, but faces obstacles from Alan's mom and Alan's frugality.

Name: Who Got Dee Pregnant?
Description: The gang panics when Dee reveals she's pregnant and they can't remember who the father might be from their previous Halloween party.

Name: A Very Sunny Christmas
Description: Dennis and Dee take inspiration from "A Christmas Carol" to teach Frank a lesson, while Mac and Charlie discover unsettling truths about their Christmas traditions from their childhood.

Name: The Maureen Ponderosa Wedding Massacre
Description: The gang becomes the primary suspects in a massacre that occurs at the McPoyle-Ponderosa wedding.

Name: The Gang Squashes Their Beefs
Description: The gang's Thanksgiving plans are ruined by their past conflicts with old enemies. In an effort to make amends, they decide to reconcile with those they have wronged.

Name: The Janitor Always Mops Twice
Description: Charlie finds himself in a black-and-white world, reliving a noir-style memory where Frank has been poisoned with diarrhea. With Frank out of commission, it's up to Charlie to navigate the seedy underbelly of Philadelphia.

Name: It's the Most Wonderful Time of the Year
Description: The Fisher family prepares for a memorable Christmas dinner with guests and surprises. Meanwhile, Brenda's sexual experimentation continues and Nate and David work on Christmas day for a biker's funeral.

Name: Halloween
Description: Jake bets Holt that he can steal his Medal of Valor before Halloween ends, and Amy has to wear a costume while undercover with Charles.

Name: Thanksgiving
Description: Amy hosts a disastrous Thanksgiving dinner for the precinct.

Name: Christmas Comes This Time Each Year
Description: Holt puts Jake in charge of his security when he receives death threats, while Terry undergoes a psych evaluation, and Amy tries to create the perfect holiday card for Holt.

Name: Halloween II
Description: Jake and Holt continue their annual Halloween bet, this time over Holt's watch. Meanwhile, Gina is kicked off her dance team and Terry confronts her about her bad attitude.

Name: Lockdown
Description: The precinct is on lockdown during Thanksgiving, and Jake is in charge of keeping everyone entertained and under control. However, things quickly become chaotic, and Amy worries that they won't be able to keep the peace.

Name: The Pontiac Bandit Returns
Description: Doug Judy is back in custody, and Rosa convinces Captain Holt to offer him a plea deal to help them track down a drug leader. Gina and Boyle are worried about their parents' relationship, and Santiago makes a Christmas gift for Holt.

Name: Halloween III
Description: Jake and Holt split the precinct into teams to compete in a challenge to steal a crown that's being guarded in the interrogation room.

Name: Yippie Kayak
Description: Jake, Charles, and Gina face a Christmas shopping disaster, while Terry hopes to avoid work during the holidays. Meanwhile, Amy participates in a cold water swim with Holt and Diaz.

Name: Halloween IV
Description: The squad competes in the annual Halloween heist for the title of Ultimate Detective Slash Genius.

Name: Mr. Santiago
Description: At Thanksgiving dinner, Amy's ex-cop father visits and Jake attempts to impress him, while Charles is left in charge of the turkey. Meanwhile, Holt aids Pimento in accepting his retirement from the police force.

Name: Captain Latvia
Description: In a bid to make Christmas special for Charles' son, Jake and Charles find themselves entangled in a dangerous situation with a Latvian criminal ring as they search for the boy's favorite toy.

Name: HalloVeen
Description: The precinct competes in their fifth annual Halloween heist, with each member vying for the title of "Amazing Human/Genius" before the clock strikes midnight.

Name: Two Turkeys
Description: Jake and Amy decide to bring their parents together for Thanksgiving.

Name: Forgiveness and Stuff
Description: After Richard Gilmore collapses at the Christmas party, he is rushed to the hospital. Lorelai and Luke go to the hospital where they join Emily and Rory who are already there.

Name: The Bracebridge Dinner
Description: Lorelai plans an extravagant Thanksgiving feast in Stars Hollow and invites the whole town to participate. She adds an Elizabethan twist to the event, with costumes and decorations to match.

Name: A Deep Fried Korean Thanksgiving
Description: Rory and Lorelai juggle four Thanksgiving dinners, leading to some humorous situations. Lorelai discovers that Rory has applied to colleges other than Harvard, causing tension between them. Lane experiences her first kiss.

Name: He's Slippin' 'Em Bread... Dig?
Description: On Thanksgiving, Luke is struggling with how to tell Lorelai about his daughter. Meanwhile, Lane's band has a showcase, and the girls try to juggle their Thanksgiving plans with their commitments to the band.

Name: A Vineyard Valentine
Description: Rory and Logan invite Lorelai and Luke to spend Valentine's Day at the Huntzberger's house on Martha's Vineyard, but tensions rise between Luke and Logan.

Name: Merry Fisticuffs
Description: Emily throws a lavish party while Luke discusses partial custody of April with a lawyer. A significant event occurs between Luke and Lorelai during the holiday season.

Name: Santa's Secret Stuff
Description: Lorelai and Christopher delay their holiday plans until Rory returns from London. Luke asks Lorelai to write a recommendation letter for his custody case.

Name: Ghost in the Machine
Description: On Halloween, Mulder and Scully investigate a possible murder by a thinking computer of a corporate executive.

Name: Christmas Carol
Description: During her Christmas vacation at her brother's home in San Diego, Scully receives a strange phone call that leads her to investigate a woman's suicide and a potential connection to Scully's deceased sister, Melissa.

Name: How the Ghosts Stole Christmas
Description: On Christmas Eve, Mulder and Scully are trapped in a haunted house with two ghosts who demonstrate the loneliness of the holiday season.

Name: Pilgrim Rick
Description: At Randall's house, the family comes together for Thanksgiving as Jack and Rebecca struggle through their own disastrous holiday.

Name: Last Christmas
Description: On Christmas, Jack and Rebecca reconnect with an old friend, and Kevin, Randall, and Kate deal with their own holiday dramas.

Name: Jack Pearson's Son
Description: Jack and Rebecca's Valentine's Day takes a turn for the worse, while Toby and Kate work through their own issues. Kevin prepares for his opening night, and Randall starts to unravel under stress.

Name: The 20's
Description: Jack and Rebecca's Halloween plans with the kids go wrong, while the Big Three have life-changing experiences on Halloween night.

Name: Six Thanksgivings
Description: The Pearsons celebrate an unconventional Thanksgiving dinner, while in the past, Jack, Rebecca, and the Big Three spend the holiday with Miguel.

Name: So Long, Marianne
Description: The Pearson family has their first Thanksgiving at Randall's Philadelphia townhouse.

Name: Taboo
Description: At Thanksgiving dinner, Rebecca has a major revelation to share with the family.

Name: Haunted
Description: Joanie expresses her fear of the haunted Simpson house, but Richie mocks her until he sees a ghostly figure in one of the closets.

Name: Guess Who's Coming to Christmas
Description: Richie discovers that Fonzie has nowhere to go for Christmas, so he invites him to join the Cunninghams. However, they are unsure if Fonzie will fit in with their family traditions.

Name: Fonsillectomy
Description: Fonzie has to spend the night in the hospital's children's ward, and he is more concerned about who will be flirting with his girlfriend at the Halloween party than his upcoming tonsillectomy.

Name: Be My Valentine
Description: The Cunninghams and their friends have a nostalgically humorous Valentine's Day celebration with music and romance.

Name: The Evil Eye
Description: When Al Delvecchio's right arm is cursed to do the bidding of an old witch with an evil eye, Richie and his friends decide to perform a Halloween exorcism to break the spell.

Name: The First Thanksgiving
Description: Marion Cunningham shares the story of the first Thanksgiving to emphasize the importance of togetherness and fellowship, rather than being glued to the TV for football, to her family.

Name: Christmas Time
Description: On a chilly, snowy Christmas in Wisconsin, Howard Cunningham persuades his family to try out a modern artificial tree, while a perplexing sailor delivers a present from Fonzie's dad.

Name: White Christmas
Description: Marion worries about Richie, Fonzie and his friends get snowed in at Al's, and Joanie tries to convince her dad to let her go to New York with Jenny.

Name: All I Want for Christmas
Description: Howard's brother visits for Christmas, causing tension, while Heather wishes for Santa's help in reuniting her mother with her estranged parents.

Name: Twas the Nightmare Before Christmas
Description: The women's holiday plans take a terrifying turn when they become hostages of a man in a Santa Claus costume at the Grief Counseling Center.

Name: Valentine's Day
Description: On Valentine's Day, the girls are stood up by their dates and end up reminiscing about their favorite past Valentine's Day memories over some cheesecake.

Name: Have Yourself a Very Little Christmas
Description: The Golden Girls decide to spend their Christmas day volunteering at a homeless shelter. While there, they discover that Stan, Dorothy's ex-husband, has been kicked out by his current wife and is now homeless.

Name: A Christmas Secret
Description: In Cabot Cove, the fiancé of a prominent family's daughter becomes a suspect in a shooting.

Name: Carol of the Bells
Description: The holiday season is in full swing in Richmond. Rebecca has a secret mission for Ted, while Roy and Keeley search for a Christmas miracle. Meanwhile, the Higginses open up their home to share in the festive spirit.

Name: The Rocky Horror Glee Show
Description: Will, consumed by jealousy, decides to produce a controversial school play - "The Rocky Horror Picture Show" - and Sue supports him for her own devious reasons.

Name: A Very Glee Christmas
Description: Finn attempts to spread holiday cheer at McKinley High while Sue dons a Grinch disguise to steal Christmas presents.

Name: Silly Love Songs
Description: The glee club's Valentine's Day kissing booth ends up causing heartbreak and disappointment when things don't go as planned.

Name: Extraordinary Merry Christmas
Description: The Glee Club faces a tough choice when they are invited to perform at two conflicting events happening at the same time.

Name: Heart
Description: Will challenges the Glee Club to find and perform the world's greatest love songs in honor of Valentine's Day.

Name: Thanksgiving
Description: Some McKinley alumni offer New Directions advice on their Sectionals performance while Rachel and Kurt have an unconventional Thanksgiving dinner.

Name: Glee, Actually
Description: Sam and Brittany enjoy their final days before the predicted Mayan apocalypse, while Kurt has a memorable Christmas.

Name: I Do
Description: On Valentine's Day, Will and Emma get married in Lima, and their union brings together both past and present members of New Directions to celebrate.

Name: Previously Unaired Christmas
Description: New Directions audition for roles in McKinley's living Nativity Scene while Rachel, Kurt, and Santana work as Santa's elves at a mall in New York. The episode was not allowed to air by FOX the previous year.

Name: Halloween
Description: In this Halloween-themed episode, Buffy and her friends visit a costume shop where the costumes seem to have a life of their own, turning customers into the characters they're dressed as.

Name: Bewitched, Bothered and Bewildered
Description: Xander tries to improve his love life through witchcraft, but his spell goes wrong and he finds himself with multiple girls competing for his affection.

Name: Amends
Description: As Christmas approaches, Angel is plagued by malevolent visions that urge him to eliminate Buffy.

Name: Fear Itself
Description: Buffy and her friends become trapped inside a haunted fraternity house on Halloween, where they encounter real bats, zombies, and a terrifying demon.

Name: Pangs
Description: On Thanksgiving, Buffy comes across the spirit of a Native American warrior whose people were annihilated by settlers.

Name: Christmas at Downton Abbey
Description: At a Christmas party in 1919, tensions rise at Downton Abbey following Bates' arrest, despite the festive atmosphere.

Name: A Journey to the Highlands
Description: The Crawleys travel to Duneagle Castle to spend Christmas with the MacClares. When they return home, a tragedy occurs that threatens to change their lives forever.

Name: A Moorland Holiday
Description: Autumn of 1924 has arrived, and the Crawley family is invited to a grouse shooting party in Northumberland by Rose's father-in-law.

Name: Christmas Special
Description: Mary tries to reconcile with her sister and Edith's secret still looms. Henry struggles to find his place at Downton as a stepfather.

Name: For Those Who Think Young
Description: On Valentine's Day, the staff of Sterling Cooper Advertising Agency hustles to check out the newest office equipment. Don and Duck clash over an account, while Betty hears from an old friend.

Name: Christmas Comes But Once a Year
Description: The firm gains a valuable new client when Freddy returns, and they reluctantly host a Christmas party for their most important client. Meanwhile, Don struggles with spending his first Christmas away from his children.

Name: Christmas Waltz
Description: In this episode, Lane struggles with a large debt while the firm hopes to win Jaguar as a client again. Meanwhile, Don tries to console Joan during a difficult time.

Name: The Doorway, Part 1
Description: Don and Megan escape to Hawaii for the holidays, while Sally entertains a friend at home. Meanwhile, Peggy's Super Bowl ad campaign is ruined by a comedian, and Roger receives devastating news about his mother.

Name: The Doorway, Part 2
Description: Don befriends his surgeon neighbor, Peggy works to salvage her campaign, Roger causes a scene at his mother's funeral, and Betty searches for Sally's friend in Manhattan.

Name: Turkey or Fish
Description: Debra attempts to establish a new tradition by hosting a Thanksgiving fish dinner for both families, but her plans are jeopardized when Marie insists on bringing a turkey.

Name: The Ball
Description: Ray's childhood memories are shattered when he finds out that the autographed Mickey Mantle baseball his father gave him is a fake, and he considers revealing the truth about Santa Claus to Ally.

Name: All I Want for Christmas
Description: Ray hopes for a romantic Christmas with Debra, but finds it challenging to make it a reality.

Name: Halloween Candy
Description: When Debra urges Ray to get a vasectomy, he decides to buy colored condoms instead. However, the plan backfires when the condoms are accidentally handed out to trick-or-treaters on Halloween.

Name: No Fat
Description: Marie plans a healthy Thanksgiving to help with her cholesterol, much to the disappointment of her family who were expecting a traditional feast with all the fixings.

Name: The Toaster
Description: When Ray gives his parents an engraved toaster for Christmas, they exchange it for a new television without even opening the gift.

Name: No Thanks
Description: Debra attempts to improve her relationship with Marie by spending the day cooking together, while Ray reluctantly agrees to take Robert and Frank to a car show.

Name: The Christmas Picture
Description: Ray plans to surprise Marie with a family picture for Christmas, but tensions rise when Marie insists that Debra's family not be included.

Name: The Tenth Anniversary
Description: Ray accidentally records football over his wedding video, causing Debra to become very angry.

Name: Fighting In-Laws
Description: During Thanksgiving, Debra's parents pay a visit and share that they are attending marriage counseling.

Name: Christmas Present
Description: In an attempt to convince Debra to let him go golfing, Ray goes all out and gets her an amazing Christmas present.

Name: Older Women
Description: Debra's father invites an older woman to Thanksgiving dinner, causing a stir among the family.

Name: Season's Greetings
Description: Marie writes a Christmas letter insulting Debra and praising herself. Raymond and Debra respond with their own letter, heavily praising Raymond and excluding Robert, who wants to add his own information.

Name: The Thought That Counts
Description: Ray lies to Debra about getting her a Christmas present, but when Robert suggests a thoughtful gift, Ray takes all the credit, causing tension between the brothers.

Name: The Bird
Description: The family joins Amy's parents for Thanksgiving, but a disagreement erupts when Pat kills a bird that hits the house.

Name: Jazz Records
Description: When Ray's twins ruin his dictionary, Frank brings up how Ray ruined his jazz records. Ray tries to make it up to him by giving him CDs instead of records for Christmas.

Name: Everybody Hates Halloween
Description: Chris attends an adult party to impress a girl who will be there, but with his friend's encouragement, he decides to dress up as the eccentric singer Prince.

Name: Everybody Hates Christmas
Description: Rochelle and Julius struggle to afford the Christmas gift that Chris wants, a new Walkman. Meanwhile, Drew decides to tell Tonya the truth about Santa Claus, causing her to question other things her parents have told her.

Name: Everybody Hates Valentine's Day
Description: Chris receives several "I hate you" cards from Caruso and becomes smitten with a girl on his bus. Julius is taken aback when Tonya reveals that she has a boyfriend, and Drew receives a bunch of Valentine's Day cards.

Name: Everybody Hates Thanksgiving
Description: Julius' accomplished younger brother joins the family for Thanksgiving dinner and Julius strives to make a flawless feast.

Name: Everybody Hates Kris
Description: Julius takes on a temporary job as Santa Claus at a department store and convinces Chris to dress up as an elf. However, things take a turn for the worse when a child wets himself while sitting on Julius' lap

Name: Everybody Hates Kwanzaa
Description: Julius convinces his family to celebrate Kwanzaa instead of Christmas to save money. Chris helps Kill Moves locate his mother as part of a school project.

Name: Everybody Hates New Year's Eve
Description: Chris wants to go to Times Square for New Year's Eve but struggles to find a way, while Julius becomes a hero for talking a jumper down from the George Washington Bridge.

Name: The Wood Who Stole Christmas
Description: Amidst the holiday season, Wood grapples with his children's materialistic attitude and decides to donate all their gifts to a less fortunate family in the neighborhood.

Name: The Thanksgiving Show
Description: Wood's cousin Alvin, who is an ex-con and the black sheep of the family, visits for Thanksgiving.

Name: I'll Be Home for Christmas
Description: Will desires an uncommon racing set for Christmas, and Herman finds it four hours away. On Christmas Eve, Herman and Wood embark on a trip to get it but end up stranded when their car malfunctions.

Name: Night of the Living Newtons
Description: Wood helps Emily overcome her fear of scary costumes by allowing her to choose his Halloween costume, while Taylor faces a crisis of confidence as an actor.

Name: The Christmas Show
Description: Ellen attempts to end her relationship with her boyfriend Greg before Christmas, but finds herself singing carols at his house instead. Meanwhile, Joe's rocky relationship with his girlfriend is affecting their work at the store.

Name: Trick or Treat - Who Cares?
Description: On Halloween, Ellen tries to lift Spence's spirits as he dwells on his failed career. Paige struggles with a movie assignment, and Joe is unnerved by Audrey's presence, who mistakenly thinks she got hired at Buy the Book.

Name: Do You Fear What I Fear?
Description: Ellen invites Spence to spend Christmas with her parents, but they have to leave town, leaving her with an unexpected gift: a cemetery burial plot.

Name: Kiss My Bum
Description: Ellen and Ed volunteer at a soup kitchen on Thanksgiving and invite a homeless worker named Perry over for dinner. Spence's mother meets Paige for the first time, and Peter misses Barrett.

Name: Fleas Navidad
Description: Ellen and Paige plan a Christmas trip to Mexico, leaving Joe and Audrey to run Buy the Book. Ellen decides to stay in town to care for a stray dog she found, but her father Harold mistakes it as a gift and takes it home with him.

Name: The Miracle of Thanksgiving
Description: The team works together to prepare Thanksgiving dinner.

Name: Our Very First Christmas Show
Description: Snowed in at an airport on Christmas Eve, the family fears they won't make it home for the holiday. Meanwhile, Stephanie worries Santa won't be able to find her.

Name: Little Shop of Sweaters
Description: D.J. and Stephanie can't replace a damaged Valentine's Day sweater, causing them to worry, while Jesse goes on a serious date with Rebecca and Joey attends a Valentine's Day ball dressed as Popeye.

Name: Happy New Year
Description: Joey struggles to find a New Year's Eve date, feeling lonely as his friends make their own plans.

Name: A Very Tanner Christmas
Description: The Tanner family is divided during Christmas with Danny missing Vicki, Rebecca missing snowy Christmases, and DJ worrying about her long-distance relationship with Steve.

Name: Arrest Ye Merry Gentlemen
Description: Michelle saves up for a special Christmas gift for her father, but Becky unknowingly buys the same gift as a joke. Meanwhile, Nicky and Alex are afraid of Santa.

Name: Dateless in San Francisco
Description: Michelle is thrilled to have a boyfriend for Valentine's Day, but Joey is also surprised to receive gifts from a secret admirer. Jesse helps Danny plan a romantic date with Claire, but Rebecca feels left out.

Name: Keeping Faith
Description: Grace and Russell rush to Alabama when Grace's sister Faith collapses at work. Faith is having an affair and Grace invites her to move closer after a Christmas visit.

Name: Valentine's Day
Description: Quentin dislikes Ryan and orders a heart-shaped pizza for Grace, causing Ryan to leave. Faith and Russell break up, while Nadine and Wade struggle with trying to conceive.

Name: Cold Turkey
Description: Jimmy invites the Kelly family to Grace's house for Thanksgiving to make up for ignoring Libby, while Nadine and Wade start a relationship.

Name: The Holidays
Description: Grace faces the challenge of dealing with her depressed ex-mother-in-law during the holidays, while also receiving an invitation from Dougie to attend a holiday party.

Name: Grace Under a Wig
Description: Grace declines Rick's offer to see an author she enjoys due to Halloween, but Jean takes over the celebration and allows Grace to perform at a coffeehouse in costume.

Name: Thanks for Nothing
Description: Grace invites Jean to Thanksgiving when Emmet is away, but Grace becomes jealous when Jean and Rick get along well.

Name: Emmet, We Hardly Knew Ye
Description: While Jean and Grace decorate the Christmas tree, Jean receives a phone call that Emmet has had a heart attack and died.

Name: The Ghost and Mrs. Kelly
Description: Grace suspects her new home is haunted due to strange events. Meanwhile, she starts dating a minister.

Name: A Holly Jolly Christmas
Description: Grace receives a surprise about Quentin during Christmas.

Name: Mother Christmas
Description: Grace's mother visits for Christmas and attempts to transform Libby into a proper young lady.

Name: Blair Waldorf Must Pie!
Description: Dan invites Serena and her family to celebrate Thanksgiving with his own family after discovering they would be spending it alone.

Name: Roman Holiday
Description: Blair's dad arrives for the holidays with a surprise guest, while Jenny and Vanessa assist Serena in planning a memorable Christmas surprise for Dan.

Name: The Magnificent Archibalds
Description: Blair's Thanksgiving traditions are ruined by her mom's new boyfriend, while Serena keeps her past a secret from Aaron, but Dan spills the beans.

Name: The Treasure of Serena Madre
Description: Serena faces an awkward Thanksgiving dinner with unexpected guests. Meanwhile, Blair suspects her mother of keeping a secret, and Jenny seeks revenge against Eric.

Name: Crazy, Cupid, Love
Description: Blair plays matchmaker on Valentine's Day while Georgina crashes Nate's party, and Serena witnesses something shocking.

Name: It's Really Complicated
Description: Serena and Dan's first Thanksgiving together is filled with drama as everyone has their own agenda.

Name: A Kanisky Christmas
Description: Nell's plan to have a family Christmas with Joey faces opposition as everyone has already made other plans.

Name: Valentine
Description: Nell's attempts to set up Valentine's Day dates for her family end in calamity.

Name: The Spirit of Christmas
Description: During the holiday season, Nell and Addy find themselves vying for the attention of the same man.

Name: Snippets
Description: Nell and the Kaniskys and their friends reflect on the past and memories during the Christmas season.

Name: Christmas in New York
Description: Nell invites Marty over for Christmas Eve when she realizes he might be alone, but her anger flares when she discovers he told Joey that Santa isn't real.

Name: Halloween Cheer
Description: George prepares for Halloween while Carmen becomes depressed when her best friend Toby moves away. Angie intervenes and helps Carmen join the cheerleading team to make new friends after George's approach fails.

Name: Meet the Cuban Parents
Description: George worries about his in-laws' opinion of him when they visit for Christmas, but he proves that he can provide for his family. He also competes with his father-in-law to give the best Christmas to the family.

Name: The Valentine's Day Massacre
Description: George and Angie confront the falsehoods that started their relationship

Name: Would You Like a Drumstick or a Kidney?
Description: George invites Manny and his family to Thanksgiving dinner with his own family, but he soon discovers that he is the only possible donor match for a kidney transplant that his father needs.

Name: Christmas Punch
Description: Max's belief in Santa Claus is shaken when he overhears his parents planning to buy him the presents he asked Santa for.

Name: A Clear and Presentless Danger
Description: In this Christmas-themed episode, George and his mother clash over their differing views on the holiday spirit. However, they come together to make Max's dream of meeting his BMX bike racing hero, Dave Mirra, a reality.

Name: Trick or Treat Me Right
Description: George and Angie play Halloween pranks, but when Benny's behavior becomes abusive, George decides to make some changes.

Name: George Is Being Elfish and Christ-misses His Family
Description: George lies to avoid visiting Angie's family for the holidays, but regrets it when he spends Christmas alone.

Name: Phone Home for the Holidays
Description: Faith and Hope initially approve of their dad's new girlfriend, but their opinion changes when she reveals that she was abducted by aliens.

Name: Silent Night, Opening Night
Description: When Faith learns her former role is being recast, Hope convinces her to direct Hayley's school play.

Name: Mismatch
Description: Faith develops romantic feelings for one of Charlie's medical colleagues.

Name: Faith Scare-Field
Description: Faith and Hope attend a Halloween party at the house of a former neighbor. However, things take a terrifying turn when they get trapped in the host's torture chamber.

Name: 9021-Uh-Oh
Description: The story recounts Faith's past Thanksgiving dinner with her family, during which she claimed to be an actress but was actually a dog walker for celebrities.

Name: Aru-Bah Humbug
Description: Faith tells Justin that Santa isn't real, but her prank backfires when she gets stuck in the chimney.

Name: The Halloween Party
Description: Faith goes on a Halloween date with a neighbor's cousin while Hope competes against him in a Halloween contest.

Name: Christmas Time
Description: Faith shocks everyone with her costly Christmas gifts that turn out to be fake.

Name: Yule Better Watch Out
Description: Tim competes with his neighbor in a Christmas decoration contest, while Jill tries to make Randy stand out in the school pageant. Mark learns a secret about Santa Claus.

Name: Baby, It's Cold Outside
Description: Tim plans a romantic getaway with Jill.

Name: Haunting of Taylor House
Description: On Tool Time, Tim scares Al by dressing up as a monster and they carve jack-o-lanterns. At home, Tim creates a haunted house for Brad's Halloween party, but Brad's date shows up with another boy.

Name: I'm Scheming of a White Christmas
Description: Tim overdoes the Christmas decorations. Brad and Randy raise money for charity but keep some for themselves, only to be caught by their parents who make them return the money.

Name: Crazy for You
Description: The Halloween pranks start, and a fan named Rose sends Tim cookies and starts calling him at home, making him worry about an obsessive fan. Meanwhile, Jill has plans to trick Tim.

Name: A Frozen Moment
Description: Tim plans to create a Santa and elf themed photo for their Christmas card by building a set. Meanwhile, on Tool Time, he constructs a bathroom specifically for men.

Name: Twas the Blight Before Christmas
Description: Mark acts in a Christmas play at school. A neighbor puts up decorations before Tim, thanks to Randy sharing secrets. Brad wants to go skiing instead of staying home for Christmas.

Name: Borland Ambition
Description: Al buys 20% of Harry's hardware store, becomes obsessed with it, and irritates everyone around him, including Ilene.

Name: Twas the Night Before Chaos
Description: Jill's mother expresses frustration when Jill's father insists on spending his retirement lounging at home during their Christmas visit.

Name: Twas the Flight Before Christmas
Description: Tim and Al go to a winter festival for Binford, but get stranded at the airport due to snow. Meanwhile, they compete in a holiday decorating contest. Al's mother wants to join them for New Year's, but Ilene gives Al an ultimatum.

Name: I Was a Teenage Taylor
Description: Brad and Randy start a prank war by placing a fake head in the microwave on Halloween. Tim and Jill retaliate by hiring an actor to play a spooky visitor. Brad and Randy pretend to be scared to fool them.

Name: The Wood, the Bad and the Hungry
Description: On Thanksgiving, Randy volunteers at a soup kitchen. Tim doesn't want to invite Benny over, but later finds out that Benny goes there for the good soup.

Name: No Place Like Home
Description: The Taylor family and Tim's brothers visit their mother's home since she is moving. They reminisce over childhood items and things the dad built, but struggle to let go when the new owners come to see the house.

Name: A Funny Valentine
Description: Tim meets his father's ex-girlfriend, but doesn't want to know more because he's worried about his father having an affair. Meanwhile, Tim loses the Valentine's Day gift he bought for Jill.

Name: Thanksgiving
Description: Tim's family is invited to spend Thanksgiving in a luxury suite at the Lions' football game.

Name: Bright Christmas
Description: Jill's mother visits for Christmas, her first one since her husband's passing. Jill struggles to see her mother with another man while Tim goes all out with his Christmas decorations.

Name: Bewitched
Description: Wilson vanishes after throwing a Halloween party with his new love interest, who claims to be a witch.

Name: Home for the Holidays
Description: Tim and Al compete in a Christmas decoration contest. Randy returns home for Christmas and notices changes.

Name: Spooky Endings
Description: Jane and Brad opt to housesit in the suburbs for a spooky Halloween, while the rest of the gang heads to a costume party at a warehouse.

Name: Grinches Be Crazy
Description: Max plays Santa Claus for Penny's charity event, but Jane accidentally donates the Christmas vacation money that Brad saved.

Name: The St. Valentine's Day Maxssacre
Description: The gang's Valentine's Day plans go awry.

Name: More Like Stanksgiving
Description: The gang celebrates Thanksgiving at Alex and Dave's new apartment while reminiscing on how they all met ten years ago.

Name: No-Ho-Ho
Description: The gang throws a birthday party for Jane, who lied about being born on Christmas and never had her own celebration.

Name: Miracle in Oaktown
Description: Mark, dressed as Santa Claus, fulfills a little boy's Christmas wish.

Name: Valentine's Day Massacre
Description: Robin and Vanessa win TV dates; Mark stays home on Valentine's Day.

Name: Santa's Got a Brand New Bag
Description: Mark and Geneva try to revive Nicole's belief in Santa, but it's no use. A mysterious cousin shows up and manages to put a smile back on Nicole's face.

Name: Christmas Show
Description: Mark's Santa gig and Christmas plans are disasters, but the holiday spirit prevails.

Name: Halloween
Description: Tyler accepts Nicole's dare to spend the night in a haunted house on Halloween, but things take a terrifying turn.

Name: Christmas '95
Description: Mark and his friends have a disappointing trip to a tree farm, but discover the true spirit of Christmas.

Name: Fairy Tales Can Come True
Description: On Halloween night, Cliff meets his dream woman at the bar, but he's too afraid to see her again without his costume. Meanwhile, Sam and Diane go on their first non-romantic outing after their breakup.

Name: House of Horrors with Formal Dining and Used Brick
Description: Carla discovers that the new house she recently purchased was built on top of a 17th-century prison graveyard, leading to a spooky Halloween night alone in the house. Cliff offers to keep her company and help her overcome her fears.

Name: Thanksgiving Orphans
Description: Diane and the gang plan a Thanksgiving potluck at Carla's new home, but things don't go according to plan when some guests don't show up and an uninvited guest crashes the party.

Name: Christmas Cheers
Description: Frasier, Lilith, Norm, Cliff, Rebecca, Carla, Woody, and Sam all have their own holiday plans and problems. Sam struggles to find a last-minute gift for Rebecca and hopes to find something appropriate yet affordable.

Name: Bar Wars V: The Final Judgement
Description: The Cheers and Gary's Olde Towne Tavern gangs have a Halloween prank war. But when Gary announces he wants a truce due to high blood pressure, Sam doesn't believe him and continues to plot. Later, Gary is found dead.

Name: Love Me, Love My Car
Description: Woody's parents give him and Kelly a pet pig, but see it as Christmas dinner. Rebecca saves the pig and wants to buy it, but when Woody refuses, she sets it free. The pig is found by Carla, who turns it into a meal.

Name: Caroline and the Balloon
Description: The gang participates in the Thanksgiving Day parade with a 'Caroline in the City' balloon, but Shelly's actions lead to chaos as the balloon gets released.

Name: Caroline and the Christmas Break
Description: Caroline and Del's holiday vacation leads to a breakup and Caroline seeks revenge. Meanwhile, Richard enlists Charlie's help to break up with Shelly, but the plan goes awry.

Name: Caroline and the Freight King
Description: Caroline gets locked in the laundry with a homeless man, Del hires a stripper-gram as a receptionist, and Charlie becomes jealous. Meanwhile, Richard tries to break up with Shelly.

Name: Caroline and the Used Car Salesman
Description: Caroline's family visits for Christmas and Richard gets a second job as a car salesman, causing rumors of infidelity.

Name: Caroline and the Decanter
Description: Richard and Julia's belated honeymoon in Hawaii is ruined when they get snowed in. Caroline has an unpleasant Christmas dinner with the Cassidys, while Charlie's father pays him a visit.

Name: Caroline and the First Date
Description: Del is tasked with organizing the firm's Halloween party, but fears it may lead to him getting fired. Meanwhile, Caroline and Richard have their first date, but struggle to agree on what to do.

Name: Caroline and the Fright Before Christmas
Description: Caroline becomes disillusioned with the commercialism of Christmas, leading the gang to try and change her mind. However, their plans don't quite go as expected.

Name: Kiss & Tell
Description: Jamie mistakenly assumes that Fancy is his date at a Halloween masquerade party.

Name: A Thanksgiving to Remember
Description: Jamie and friends' failed promotion teaches them the importance of gratitude.

Name: Misery Loves Company
Description: On Halloween, Jamie is propositioned by a hotel guest who wants him to be her eternal husband. Junior and Helen have an unexpected experience at a lovers' retreat.

Name: Christmas Day-Ja Vu
Description: Jamie experiences a Christmas Eve time loop and gains a new appreciation for the holiday's true meaning.

Name: The Christmas Wedding
Description: Lionel and Jenny's Christmas wedding plans face opposition from George, who disapproves of their minister's religious denomination and skin color.

Name: 984 W. 124th Street, Apt. 5C
Description: Louise discovers George has been making monthly payments to an address in Harlem.

Name: George Finds a Father
Description: During the Christmas holiday, George learns a disturbing secret about his mother from his guardian.

Name: Now You See It, Now You Don't: Part 1
Description: On Halloween night, Louise witnesses a man dressed as a rabbit committing murder, turning the evening of dressing up as movie stars into a night of terror.

Name: Now You See It, Now You Don't: Part 2
Description: George and friends wait for the costume contest at the bar, but Louise confronts the killer rabbit in her apartment, becoming his next target.

Name: All I Want for Christmas
Description: George, dressed as Santa Claus at the Help Center, makes a promise to ten-year-old orphan Billy to fulfill his Christmas wish for a pair of parents.

Name: Father Christmas
Description: Louise, Helen and Bentley go caroling while George and Tom decline, saying it's for women. George and Tom bond over Christmas stories about their fathers.

Name: Joey and the Plot Twist
Description: Joey struggles to get into the Christmas spirit in California, while Gina has given up on Christmas since her son Michael lost Christmas faith at age three. Meanwhile, on his new show "Powder Deep," Joey's character may be killed off after he upsets the obsessive producer.

Name: Joey and the Valentine's Date
Description: Joey mistakenly leads a reporter to believe he's serious about a Valentine's Day flirtation to secure a good review in People Magazine.

Name: Joey and the Bachelor Thanksgiving
Description: Joey's plans to show his finished villa to Alex are ruined when Gina takes over for a Thanksgiving decoration frenzy. Meanwhile, Joey is charmed by his party-loving neighbor Dean, and Zach and Joey must retrieve donated archaeological artifacts from a poor family.

Name: Joey and the Christmas Party
Description: Joey struggles to resist his attraction to Alex while throwing a Christmas party with plenty of young, desirable guests. Meanwhile, Bobbie deals with an overbearing British man and Michael and Zack struggle to impress girls.

Name: Jesus, It's Christmas
Description: Maya suggests pooling Christmas money to give to someone in need, but is stunned when janitor Jesus uses the money to buy her lavish gifts. Finch steals a camera lens to get invited to a swimsuit shoot.

Name: The Mask
Description: Finch thinks Nina has an imaginary alter ego, while Maya learns Jack deceived her on Halloween years ago.

Name: How the Finch Stole Christmas
Description: Finch is disappointed with his Christmas present and decides to swap everyone's presents with lame objects in retaliation.

Name: The First Thanksgiving
Description: Thanksgiving at Jack's country house.

Name: Christmas? Christmas!
Description: Jack's daughter Hannah causes a scene while waiting to see Santa, and Jack must intervene. Maya meets a celebrity who shares her love for Christmas, but takes it to an extreme level.

Name: Halloween? Halloween!
Description: Blush team attends Nina's A-list Halloween party, where Jack and Finch compete for the attention of a model. Maya helps Elliott realize his true feelings for Vicky, Nina becomes jealous of her new boyfriend's past lovers.

Name: New Year's Eve
Description: Kate and Allie search for New Year's Eve plans, hoping to avoid spending the night alone at home.

Name: Thanksgiving
Description: Allie hosts Thanksgiving with Charles' new wife Claire, but guests cancel and Charles is called to work, leaving Allie and Claire to bond.

Name: Halloween II
Description: Kate and Allie accidentally bring home a man and his ex-wife's ghost on Halloween night after attending a parade.

Name: The Nightmare Before Christmas
Description: The family swaps traditional Christmas for a ski trip and offers to be helper elves for others' holiday celebrations.

Name: Supermarket Story
Description: Doug, Carrie, and Arthur have an eventful day grocery shopping for Thanksgiving.

Name: Noel Cowards
Description: During the Christmas season, Doug and Carrie dream of buying a new car but realize they can't afford it. Unexpectedly, Arthur surprises them with a generous gift.

Name: S'ain't Valentine's
Description: Veronica throws a surprise party for Spence, interrupting Doug's romantic plans with Carrie. Meanwhile, Arthur meets a woman at a Senior Center dance.

Name: Roamin' Holiday
Description: Doug wants to spend a quiet Thanksgiving with Carrie but when her friends want to stay for the weekend, he convinces Spence to move out and stay with them until he finds a place of his own.

Name: Net Prophets
Description: Doug and Carrie invest in stock for Christmas, but it causes them more stress than joy. Meanwhile, Arthur wants to go all out with Christmas decorations.

Name: Meet By-Product
Description: On Valentine's Day, Doug and Carrie reflect on how they initially didn't hit it off when they first met.

Name: Dark Meet
Description: Doug, Carrie, and Arthur reminisce about their first Thanksgiving together with Arthur's second wife, Lily.

Name: Better Camera
Description: During the Christmas season, the Heffernans discover that their new neighbor is Lou Ferrigno.

Name: Ticker Treat
Description: Doug accidentally causes Arthur to have a minor heart attack on Halloween.

Name: Loaner Car
Description: Deacon wants to give his kids a great Thanksgiving, but he can't do it alone. Doug offers to lend Carrie's help, but Deacon quickly discovers that she's more than he bargained for.

Name: Mentalo Case
Description: The approaching Christmas brings about confusion over gift-giving and what each person will receive.

Name: Animal Attraction
Description: On Valentine's Day, Doug's plans with Carrie are ruined when he and Deacon have to make an unexpected trip to deliver two penguins to Albany.

Name: Thanks, Man
Description: On Thanksgiving, a man with a broken-down car asks to use Doug's phone. Carrie is suspicious of him.

Name: Santa Claustrophobia
Description: Carrie takes a temporary job at IPS, leading Doug to feel like she's always around him. Meanwhile, Arthur wants a family Christmas photo and is willing to include anyone in it.

Name: Silent Mite
Description: Doug thinks someone of small stature stole his wallet.

Name: Last Halloween Standing
Description: Mike feels let down when his daughters aren't into Halloween anymore. He sneaks his grandson Boyd out to go trick or treating, but his daughter Kristin is against it.

Name: Last Christmas Standing
Description: Ryan's unexpected return to town dampens Mike's Christmas spirit while causing confusion for Kristin and Kyle. At the same time, Mandy tries to unionize other elves as an elf at Outdoor Man, where Ed hired her.

Name: Putting a Hit on Christmas
Description: Mike wants to surprise Vanessa with a stress-free Christmas by taking their family on a holiday trip, but Ed accidentally shoots a bald eagle while hunting for a turkey.

Name: Haunted House
Description: Vanessa runs the Halloween Haunted House at Boyd's school but it ends up being too scary for him. Meanwhile, Mandy hurts Eve's feelings by telling her she's not popular.

Name: Thanksgiving
Description: Bud shocks the Baxters on Thanksgiving by revealing his plan to open a recreational marijuana store, leaving Mike torn between supporting his father and the values he wants to instill in his family.

Name: Elfie
Description: Mandy surprises the housekeeper for Christmas, while Ryan considers spoiling the magic of the season for Boyd, but Mike thinks otherwise.

Name: Tasers
Description: Vanessa receives a bouquet of roses on Valentine's Day, but she knows they're not from Mike since he doesn't believe in giving flowers on a holiday created by Hallmark.

Name: Wedding Planning
Description: Mike and Vanessa offer to give Kristin and Ryan a generous wedding present, but there's a catch. Meanwhile, Kyle asks Ed to teach him how to play poker.

Name: Halloween
Description: Mike and Chuck skip giving out Halloween candy to watch football, prompting a prank war with Vanessa and Carol. Kyle dresses up like Ed at Outdoor Man, but Ed feels insulted by the impersonations.

Name: The Gratitude List
Description: Vanessa is disappointed when Eve bypasses one of their holiday traditions on Thanksgiving. Kristin discovers that Mandy is lying about where she and Kyle will spend Thanksgiving.

Name: Gift of the Wise Man
Description: Mike challenges his family to do a good deed for Vanessa during Christmas, while Chuck becomes Outdoor Man's Santa.

Name: Trick or Treat
Description: The family plans their Halloween party, but Mike is unhappy with the holiday and picks a theme where they dress up as each other. Bickering ensues, but they come together to support Vanessa, who has just been laid off.

Name: My Name Is Rob
Description: Eve brings her new boyfriend to the Baxter family Christmas dinner.

Name: Bride of Prankenstein
Description: On Halloween, Mike and Chuck are installing a security system at Outdoor Man when they decide to prank Joe. Meanwhile, Mandy, Kyle, Kristin, and Ryan organize a seance to communicate with the supernatural.

Name: The Gift of the Mike Guy
Description: Mike searches for a meaningful Christmas gift for Ed, while Eve visits home and Vanessa reminds the family about the value of their holiday traditions.

Name: The Best Man
Description: Mike is torn between his desire to officiate Chuck and Carol's wedding vow renewal for their 25th anniversary and his wish to be Chuck's best man.

Name: Oh Hear the Angels' Voices
Description: Laverne, Shirley, and their group of friends perform at a Christmas party for patients in the hospital.

Name: New Year's Eve 1959
Description: On New Year's Eve 1959, Laverne's date cancels, Shirley is sick, and Lenny and Squiggy have a plan for midnight. Will the night end in tears or cheers for Laverne?

Name: O Come All Ye Bums
Description: The girls and their friends help Frank keep the holiday spirit alive for the less fortunate after he has to cancel his yearly gathering for the homeless and poor.

Name: One Office Party Too Many
Description: At the Christmas party, everyone comes with a plan but ends up unable to carry it out.

Name: Valentine's Day
Description: Claude has phone sex on Will's phone; Lydia has a secret admirer; Owen's crush only wants him to father her child.

Name: Claude's Alternative Thanksgiving
Description: Owen's two lesbian moms come to visit for Thanksgiving and think Owen is gay. Owen asks his friends to play along, including Carl posing as his lover. Lydia and Kipp get invited to Will's party.

Name: Santa Claude
Description: Claude handles all of Will's Christmas gift shopping for his staff and girlfriend.

Name: Knock, Knock, Who's Dead?
Description: Claude tries to return Mr. Henry's belongings to his family. Ramona wants his office, but Owen scares her away with special effects. Lydia and Jeb argue over their Halloween costumes.

Name: Mom's the Word
Description: Owen's moms visit GNB for Thanksgiving, Judith encourages Carl and Ramona's bad habits. Claude worries about losing her job and Lydia has a bad Thanksgiving with Jeb's family.

Name: Claude's 15 Minutes of Christmas
Description: Claude faces challenges while organizing the GNB holiday greeting, Lydia refuses to rearrange her holiday plans, and Kipp deals with relationship turbulence during the holidays.

Name: Living Kringle
Description: Synclaire's friends are lacking enthusiasm for Christmas, which makes her sad. Despite this, she makes an effort to inspire everyone and get them into the holiday spirit.

Name: Mystery Date
Description: Overton and Synclaire's relationship is strained by bad advice from friends and competition from other suitors. Kyle throws a party to bring them back together and let Hamilton choose between the ladies.

Name: Trick or Trust
Description: Gang fails to scare Maxine on Halloween.

Name: Thanks for Giving
Description: The gang is getting ready for Thanksgiving when Scooter tells Khadijah that he needs to talk to her about something important. She assumes he is going to propose to her.

Name: Let It Snow, Let It Snow, Let It Snow... Dammit
Description: The group goes on a Christmas trip to the mountains, but Overton is unhappy when a ranger won't allow him to continue his family's holiday traditions.

Name: Doctor in the House
Description: Guests insult Khadijah at an awards banquet, while Regine tries to impress them to snag a rich man. Max overspends on herself and gives lousy gifts to others.

Name: Tis the Season
Description: Michael and Joey use their creativity to lift Nicole's spirits during Christmas, as she struggles with missing her mother.

Name: Thanks for the Memories
Description: Joey and Michael get stuck in an elevator and reminisce about their past, while Nicole, Margaret, and Shelby struggle to wait for them to be rescued before eating dinner.

Name: I'm Dreaming of a Holiday Episode
Description: Joey and Michael bicker as Christmas begins, but they imagine alternate futures where everyone is much older, except the judge who remains the same age.

Name: Murphy's Pony
Description: Murphy is irritated when three children show up at FYI two days before Christmas with a note from their mother saying she can no longer care for them and thinks Murphy would make a good mother.

Name: Why Do Fools Fall in Love?
Description: Frank and Murphy set each other up on blind dates, while Miles copes with his recent breakup with Jackie and Jim is pursued by an attractive woman. Phil's marriage issues are also revealed.

Name: What Are You Doing New Year's Eve?
Description: As New Year's Eve approaches, the gang reminisces about Murphy's past before sobriety, while Corky plans a party. Meanwhile, Murphy is home alone and struggles with the decision of whether or not to drink again.

Name: Jingle Hell, Jingle Hell, Jingle All the Way
Description: Murphy suggests her coworkers donate to charity instead of exchanging Christmas gifts, but she secretly buys presents anyway causing her coworkers to frantically purchase items at the last minute.

Name: Mission Control
Description: Murphy and her friends volunteer at a homeless shelter on Thanksgiving.

Name: I'm Dreaming of a Brown Christmas
Description: Murphy plans to have a perfect Christmas with her son and carry out every tradition, but the arrival of her father and Aunt Brooke, who have a long-standing feud, causes chaos.

Name: Brown in Toyland
Description: Murphy goes to great lengths to find a rare toy on Avery's Christmas wish list to make his holiday memorable.

Name: Old Flames
Description: Murphy has a nightmare where she is put on trial for how she treated her ex-lovers.

Name: Thanksgiving and Taking
Description: Murphy's Thanksgiving dinner guests are apprehensive about what to expect.

Name: Happy New Year
Description: The gang attempts to divert Murphy's attention from worrying about Avery's assignment in Kabul by inviting her to attend the 100th anniversary New Year's Eve celebration at Phil's Bar.

Name: Undeck the Halls
Description: Phil and Claire cancel Christmas for their kids until they confess to their wrongdoings. Jay doesn't want to celebrate Gloria and Manny's holiday traditions, while Mitchell and Cameron take Lily to meet Santa.

Name: My Funky Valentine
Description: Jay treats Gloria to a comedy show, Mitchell and Cameron play matchmakers for Manny, and Phil and Claire plan a romantic escape to spice things up.

Name: Halloween
Description: The family helps Claire with Halloween, Jay and Manny tease Gloria, and Cameron deals with painful memories during the holiday.

Name: Bixby's Back
Description: Phil and Claire reenact an old Valentine's Day routine, while Jay plans a surprise dinner for Gloria, and Mitchell and Cameron have a disagreement over Mitchell's assistant's crush. Manny advises Haley about relationships.

Name: Punkin Chunkin
Description: Phil feels creatively stifled by Claire, while Mitchell doubts Cameron's "punkin chunkin" story. Gloria won't let Jay criticize Manny's Thanksgiving centerpiece, and Haley and Alex have an accident.

Name: Express Christmas
Description: The family celebrates "Express Christmas" on December 16 when they realize they won't be together on Christmas Day.

Name: Open House of Horrors
Description: On Halloween night, Claire tries to spook Phil, Cameron flaunts his weight loss at his party, and Mitchell's falsehood about Lily's mother has consequences.

Name: New Year's Eve
Description: On New Year's Eve, the family has different plans: Jay plays poker with Billy Dee Williams, Phil and Claire attempt to rekindle their romance, Mitchell and Cameron search for a bar where they fit in, while Haley and Alex babysit.

Name: Heart Broken
Description: Phil and Claire's Valentine's plans go awry, Jay and Gloria try to be intimate after the baby, and Mitchell has a wild night after drinking at his party.

Name: The Old Man & the Tree
Description: Phil and Luke aim for Canada on the elliptical machine, Jay and Manny search for a wild Christmas tree, Gloria is jealous of Claire's mom, and a mix-up puts Cam and Lily with the homeless at Christmas.

Name: Halloween 3: AwesomeLand
Description: The family prepares for Halloween: Phil takes over decorating duties, Jay is unhappy with his costume, and Mitchell has a problem in court with a scary stenographer.

Name: Three Turkeys
Description: Phil and Luke take on Thanksgiving, but Claire has a backup plan. Jay and Gloria's plans go awry. Cameron struggles to get Lily to wear a dress.

Name: Valentine's Day 4: Twisted Sister
