Description: Claire struggles to come to terms with Phil's attraction to her alter-ego, Juliana, while Gloria's sister makes a move on Jay. Meanwhile, Mitch and Cam try to retrieve a stolen gift for their friend Anders.

Name: White Christmas
Description: Gloria plans a "White Christmas" for the family, but the weather doesn't cooperate. Jay decides the future of his business, Alex makes a new friend, and Haley and Andy keep their secret romance going.

Name: Halloween 4: The Revenge of Rod Skyhook
Description: The Dunphy's prepare for Luke's Halloween party, Cam confronts his Halloween nemesis, and Jay plans to deliver an unforgettable trick at an old enemy's party.

Name: Thanksgiving Jamboree
Description: Cameron goes all out for his Thanksgiving celebration, while Hayley opts to spend the holiday with her new boyfriend instead of her family. Jay works on keeping his blood pressure under control, and Alex grows closer to Dwight.

Name: Snow Ball
Description: Manny and Luke organize the school's winter dance, but a texting error complicates things. While Gloria, Claire, Mitchell, and Cameron volunteer at the dance, Jay pretends he wants to spend time with Phil to avoid it.

Name: It's the Great Pumpkin, Phil Dunphy
Description: Phil and Claire turn Halloween into an adult holiday, while Mitch confronts Jay about the slow kitchen renovation and Cam oversteps his welcome as a house guest.

Name: Winner Winner Turkey Dinner
Description: On Thanksgiving, everyone celebrates their victories while hiding the truth that they all cheated to achieve them.

Name: Written in the Stars
Description: Mitch and Cam interfere with Luke's date on Valentine's Day, while Jay and Gloria try some role-playing to spice up their love life. Meanwhile, Joe develops a crush on Claire.

Name: Good Grief
Description: The Dunphy-Pritchett-Tucker family experiences a Halloween full of surprises and unexpected news, with everyone dressed in costumes and enjoying tricks and treats.

Name: Stuck in a Moment
Description: Haley plans the perfect time to give her family an unforgettable Christmas gift; Phil borrows the family Christmas tree for a house showing; Jay, Gloria, and Joe handle unexpected holiday guests.

Name: The Last Halloween
Description: Phil aims to frighten Claire on Halloween; Gloria feels insecure about her age when someone assumes she is Jay's wife; Mitchell and Cameron take Lily to a carnival after she chooses to go to her first Halloween party alone.

Name: The Last Thanksgiving
Description: Cam and Mitch's friends think they broke up; Haley cooks Thanksgiving dinner; Jay takes Phil and Dylan to fly his model plane.

Name: The Last Christmas
Description: Mitchell is suspicious of Cameron's intentions for Christmas dinner; Claire avoids Jay's job offer; Luke faces the aftermath of kissing Manny's ex-girlfriend.

Name: A Melrose Place Christmas
Description: Alison recovers while Billy becomes overprotective; Jo and Jake deal with her past; Rhonda goes skiing with Terrance; Matt reconciles with his father; Michael invites co-worker Kimberly to the Christmas party.

Name: Cold Turkey
Description: Jake faces an FBI dilemma over illegal car sales. Sydney turns down Lauren's offer but attends her Thanksgiving dinner. Michael recovers from injury, and Kimberly's comatose mother arrives to take her back to Cleveland.

Name: Under the Mistletoe
Description: Alison and Billy reconnect on Christmas Eve. Sydney decides to leave her former life behind. Matt hosts a Christmas party for residents as Katya and Nikki leave for Russia.

Name: The Days of Wine and Vodka
Description: Alison insults Billy and Susan at Thanksgiving; Jake is extorted and beaten up; Sydney makes a deal with Chris; Kimberly proposes a solution to Jo's custody case; Peter anonymously buys D&D's stock.

Name: Holiday on Ice
Description: Jo gets Matt's help to get her baby back from Michael. Amanda learns a Christmas lesson from Bruce's ghost and breaks up with Peter. Matt ends things with Jeffrey, while Terry supports Alison in rehab.

Name: St. Valentine's Day Massacre
Description: Sydney is in a cult and tries to escape, Amanda works during chemotherapy, Kimberly doubts Michael, Billy confides in Alison about Amanda's health, and Matt takes Jo on a photo tour where he beats up a drug dealer.

Name: Oy! to the World
Description: Sydney hosts a holiday fundraiser at Bobby's mansion, Alison relapses into drinking, Michael discovers Kimberly is advising Sydney, and Matt enters into a new relationship.

Name: Crazy Love
Description: Peter catches Amanda with Craig, Jake and Alison's vacation turns into a nightmare, and Sydney meets a millionaire at an art auction.

Name: A Tree Talks in Melrose
Description: Cooper intervenes in Michael's divorce, Jennifer blackmails Lexi, Jon Secada helps save the Jazz Club, Connie tries to break up Samantha and Billy, and Amanda tries to reconcile with Kyle.

Name: The Usual Santas
Description: During Christmas Michael, Peter, Kyle, Ryan, and Lou Visconti are mistakenly arrested on their way to a kids charity fundraiser. Lexi, Amanda, and Eve clear up the misunderstanding.

Name: You Better Watch Out
Description: The Bundys' Christmas is disrupted when a Santa Claus who was parachuting crashes into their backyard, attracting the attention of the neighborhood kids.

Name: Peggy Loves Al - Yeah, Yeah, Yeah
Description: On Valentine's Day, Kelly gets lots of Valentine's cards, Steve plans a Hawaii trip for Marcy, and Bud waits for his first Valentine. Peggy wants Al to say "I Love You." Marcy plans to surprise Steve by jumping out of a cake.

Name: It's a Bundyful Life Part 1
Description: Al has saved up money to buy his family Christmas presents, but a late rush of customers at the shoe store prevents him from getting to the bank to retrieve the money he needs.

Name: It's a Bundyful Life Part 2
Description: Al's guardian angel visits him to show him what life would be like if he had never been born. The Jablonskys are a perfect family, while the Rhoades are similar to the Bundys, but without Al.

Name: Christmas
Description: Al avoids buying gifts for his family by pitting them against each other, but this year they make him take jobs to earn money. Playing Santa at the mall is one of the jobs, where Marcy and Jefferson taunt him.

Name: Take My Wife, Please
Description: Peggy dons a Grim Reaper costume and refuses to leave Al until someone in the family asks for him. Marcy throws a party where the Bundys dress up as the Village People to celebrate female spouse murderers.

Name: The Worst Noel
Description: Kelly and Bud sneak in a jukebox for their arguing parents on Christmas Eve while Marcy and Jefferson throw a party next door without telling Al.

Name: Valentine's Day Massacre
Description: On Valentine's Day, Al competes with other last-minute shoppers for gifts at a store. Bud searches for his long-lost Valentine, who is now a famous pop star and faces physical and sexual abuse while staying at a hotel.

Name: I Can't Believe It's Butter
Description: Griff develops feelings for a phone sex partner named "Butter" during Christmas, only to find out that "Butter" is actually Peg's mother, which Al eventually discovers.

Name: A Bundy Thanksgiving
Description: On Thanksgiving, Al and Griff visit Al's aunt Maddie to buy her famous potato pie, only to find out she has passed away. Meanwhile, Jefferson struggles to find a turkey for Marcy, but Kelly brings home a stray turkey.

Name: God Help Ye Merry Bundymen
Description: Al resists getting a Christmas tree, Marcy competes in a decorating contest, and Bud and Kelly kidnap Mary and Joseph from Marcy's Nativity Scene for ransom. Meanwhile, Gary considers replacing Al and Griff at the shoe store.

Name: Halloween Approximately
Description: Francis is late for Halloween, but he and his brothers still manage to pull off the ultimate prank. Meanwhile, Hal becomes obsessed with catching a speeder and ends up stealing the culprit's car with Lois.

Name: Christmas
Description: The Wilkerson family Christmas is in chaos as the boys misbehave, and Lois holds Christmas hostage in the garage. Meanwhile, Francis visits his grandmother in Canada, who has no Christmas spirit left.

Name: Thanksgiving
Description: Reese enlists Hal and Dewey to help with the cooking, and Francis and Piama are at odds. Meanwhile, Malcolm attends a party at Kirsten's house and declares it the best Thanksgiving ever.

Name: Christmas Trees
Description: Hal and the boys compete with the local church over Christmas tree prices during the holiday season.

Name: Hal's Christmas Gift
Description: Hal and Lois go for handmade Christmas gifts due to their financial situation, but Hal is embarrassed when he sees the boys' high-quality and thoughtful gifts, making him panic about his own shoddy attempt.

Name: Halloween
Description: Reese and Malcolm learn about a murder that took place in their house and Hal is terrified of ghosts. Meanwhile, Reese and Dewey take Jamie trick or treating and make an enemy, and Lois gets stuck at work because of a shoplifter.

Name: Halloween
Description: Corporate pressure Michael to fire an employee, casting a shadow over the office Halloween party.

Name: Christmas Party
Description: In an effort to save the office Halloween party from boredom, Michael defies corporate policy and buys alcohol for the staff.

Name: Valentine's Day
Description: Michael visits Dunder Mifflin corporate headquarters in New York with Jan, and they both get surprised. Scranton office celebrates Valentine's Day in a grade school style.

Name: A Benihana Christmas
Description: Pam and Karen host a rival Christmas party after trouble arises within the party planning committee, but Michael is not interested in celebrating as he was recently dumped by Carol.

Name: Moroccan Christmas
Description: At the office Christmas party, Phyllis blackmails Angela to take over the planning, while Dwight monopolizes a popular Christmas gift. Meredith gets drunk and sets her hair on fire, leading to an intervention from Michael.

Name: Secret Santa
Description: Michael is upset when Jim promises Phyllis the role of office Santa, while bad news from David Wallace threatens to overshadow the Christmas party.

Name: Costume Contest
Description: Halloween at Dunder Mifflin, Michael is upset with Darryl. Jim and Pam try to figure out why Danny didn't call Pam back four years ago.

Name: Classy Christmas
Description: Michael throws a Christmas party to welcome Holly back to the Scranton branch, but is disappointed to learn she still has a boyfriend.

Name: PDA
Description: Michael and Holly's PDA annoys the office, Erin solves Gabe's riddles to find her gift from Andy, and Jim and Pam get drunk and try to find a private place in the office.

Name: Spooked
Description: Erin fears she'll be fired after planning a disastrous Halloween party for Robert and his son. Meanwhile, Robert challenges the staff to come up with the perfect spooky story.

Name: Christmas Wishes
Description: Andy tries to fulfill everyone's Christmas wishes, while Robert California drowns his sorrows at the office party

Name: Special Project
Description: Andy assigns Dwight to lead a special project in Tallahassee, but Dwight is not pleased with the team Andy has put together. Meanwhile, Darryl is trying to decipher the meaning of Val's Valentine's gift.

Name: Here Comes Treble
Description: Andy hosts the Cornell a Capella group on Halloween, while Dwight discovers that Nellie takes anxiety pills and Pam disapproves of Jim's business decision.

Name: Dwight Christmas
Description: Dwight throws a Pennsylvania Dutch Christmas party but ends it early due to Jim's other job. Erin seeks comfort from a co-worker after a disappointing text from Andy.

Name: Couples Discount
Description: Andy comes back to a hostile work environment and a furious girlfriend after being gone for three months. Meanwhile, Jim's Valentine's Day plans with Pam don't go according to plan.

Name: And the Very Christmas Thanksgiving
Description: Caroline and Max work at a department store's Santaland during Caroline's first holiday season without money to earn extra cash.

Name: And the High Holidays
Description: Desperate to pay their overdue rent, Max and Caroline turn to a group of shady customers who are willing to pay top dollar for their cupcakes.

Name: And a Loan for Christmas
Description: Max and Caroline secure a bank loan to manufacture their cupcake T-shirts for high-end boutiques, while Sophie convinces the diner crew to dress up for a holiday decorating competition.

Name: Up All Night
Description: Liz forces staff to work on Valentine's Day, receives mystery flowers. Jack finalizes divorce with Bianca and celebrates with Tracy who is role-playing in a hotel room. Jack brings a hooker there.

Name: Ludachristmas
Description: Jack finds solace in the love and support of Liz's parents, while Kenneth disrupts the staff's plans for a wild holiday party.

Name: Christmas Special
Description: Jack accidentally hits his mother with his car and is forced to care for her while she recovers. To lift her spirits, he puts on a Christmas special with the help of the staff. Meanwhile, Liz buys toys for a 'Letters to Santa' program as her mother is not hosting a family Christmas.

Name: St. Valentine's Day
Description: Liz's Valentine's Day doesn't go as planned with Dr. Baird, Elisa drags Jack to church, and Kenneth goes on a date with a blind woman with Tracy's help.

Name: Secret Santa
Description: Jack reunites with a former crush from a social networking site, the writers create a fake religion to avoid participating in Secret Santa with Kenneth, and Pete seeks revenge on Jenna for not contributing to a Christmas gift.

Name: Anna Howard Shaw Day
Description: On Valentine's Day, Liz is stranded after her oral surgery, Jack goes on a date with a journalist, and Jenna confronts her stalker's infidelity.

Name: Christmas Attack Zone
Description: Jack invites his father and Avery to Christmas dinner to ambush his mother, Jenna misses her ex on "New Queers Eve", and Tracy tries to maintain his new "serious" image.

Name: Hey, Baby, What's Wrong?: Part 1
Description: Liz and Criss go to IKEA and encounter relationship problems, Jack develops an attraction to his mother-in-law, Kenneth trains his assistant, and Jenna experiences stage fright.

Name: Hey, Baby, What's Wrong?: Part 2
Description: Criss and Liz go shopping for a dining room table on Valentine's Day, while Jack spends time with his mother-in-law. Meanwhile, Jenna scrambles to find a replacement producer for her upcoming live performance, and Tracy and Frank help Lutz find a date for Valentine's Day.

Name: Gobble, Gobble, Dick, Dick
Description: The Solomons, unfamiliar with the concept of Thanksgiving, receive help from Mrs. Dubcek and her daughter Vicky to celebrate the holiday.

Name: Jolly Old St. Dick
Description: In their first Christmas on Earth, the Solomons try to understand the holiday traditions and gift-giving, while Dick struggles to find the perfect gift for Mary.

Name: Happy New Dick!
Description: Tommy throws a New Year's Eve party at the bar where Harry is employed, but Dick is feeling unaccomplished and unsure about his past year.

Name: Dick Puts the 'Id' in Cupid
Description: Dick becomes insecure after discovering that Mary has been discussing their relationship with a therapist.

Name: Fear and Loathing in Rutherford
Description: Sally and Harry attempt to assist Tommy in getting over his lost love.

Name: He Is Risen
Description: Tony and Ralphie's animosity intensifies until they are forced to confront each other. Meadow starts dating Jackie's son and finds herself in a dangerous situation.

Name: To Save Us All from Satan's Power
Description: Tony experiences flashbacks of Pussy's betrayal and grows concerned about Jackie Jr.'s failure to meet his responsibilities.

Name: Kaisha
Description: Tony and Phil clash, resulting in Phil's hospitalization. Meanwhile, Tony and Christopher find themselves romantically involved with the same woman.

Name: Hungry Man
Description: Dexter delves deeper into Arthur's dark psyche while Rita prepares Thanksgiving dinner for their guests. Debra investigates Trinity, and Batista closes an old case.

Name: Do You See What I See?
Description: Dexter struggles to balance his life with Hannah and his relationship with Debra, as Christmas draws near. Meanwhile, he discovers that the man behind his mother's murder has been released from prison.

Name: The Middle Earth Paradigm
Description: The guys attend Penny's Halloween party, but Leonard has a tense encounter with Penny's ex-boyfriend Kurt.

Name: The Bath Item Gift Hypothesis
Description: Leonard becomes jealous when Penny takes an interest in a handsome physicist at the university. Meanwhile, Sheldon struggles to choose the perfect Christmas gift for Penny.

Name: The Maternal Congruence
Description: Leonard's mother pays a visit, much to Leonard's chagrin and Sheldon's excitement

Name: The Large Hadron Collision
Description: Leonard is invited to visit the CERN laboratory in Switzerland on Valentine's Day, and Sheldon competes with Penny to be his guest.

Name: The Good Guy Fluctuation
Description: Sheldon tries to scare the gang after they play a prank on him for Halloween. Leonard seeks Penny's advice when an attractive comic book artist shows interest in him.

Name: The Holographic Excitation
Description: Raj organizes Stuart's Halloween party at the comic book store while Howard's constant talk about space annoys the gang. Meanwhile, Penny makes an effort to take an interest in Leonard's work.

Name: The Santa Simulation
Description: The girls take Raj out to a nightclub to help him find a date. Meanwhile, a game of Dungeons and Dragons brings back memories of Santa Claus for Sheldon.

Name: The Tangible Affection Proof
Description: Sheldon enlists Alex's help to buy a Valentine's Day gift for Amy. Leonard, Penny, Howard, and Bernadette have a disastrous dinner together. Raj and Stuart host a "Lonely People" party at the comic book store

Name: The Thanksgiving Decoupling
Description: The gang decides to spend Thanksgiving at Mrs. Wolowitz's house, but Sheldon is unhappy about the holiday, and tensions rise when Penny's ex-boyfriend shows up.

Name: The Cooper Extraction
Description: Sheldon goes back home to Texas for the holidays. The absence of Sheldon causes the group to appreciate his unique personality and contribution to their friendships.

Name: The Locomotive Manipulation
Description: Sheldon and Amy go on a train ride to Napa Valley with Howard and Bernadette for Valentine's Day. Meanwhile, Leonard and Penny take care of Raj's dog.

Name: The Clean Room Infiltration
Description: Amy hosts a traditional Victorian Christmas Eve dinner for the gang, while Raj's father visits from India. The guys try to get rid of a bird they accidentally let into the university clean room.

Name: The Platonic Permutation
Description: Sheldon and Amy try to spend time together as friends and visit an aquarium on Thanksgiving. Howard agrees to volunteer at the soup kitchen with Bernadette, Raj, and Emily.

Name: The Valentino Submergence
Description: Sheldon and Amy host a Valentine's Day edition of "Fun with Flags". Leonard and Penny come to terms with the challenges of aging. Meanwhile, Howard and Bernadette discover a surprise in their hot tub.

Name: The Holiday Summation
Description: The gang share stories about their holiday breaks. Sheldon and Amy talk about their trip to Texas, Leonard and Penny share their Christmas tree adventure, and Howard and Bernadette discuss their experiences as new parents.

Name: The Imitation Perturbation
Description: Wolowitz dresses up as Sheldon for Halloween and Sheldon seeks revenge. Leonard is surprised when Penny doesn't remember their first kiss.

Name: That Holiday Spirit
Description: Dominique joins the Carringtons for a Christmas gala. The party is highlighted by an announcement from Blake, which draws a lot of attention.

Name: Escape from Witch Island
Description: Dawson enlists friends to shoot a documentary for history class about a local haunted spot. As they work, tales of love and witches make Dawson and Joey reflect on their relationship while Jen and Pacey develop a new bond.

Name: Guess Who's Coming to Dinner
Description: On Thanksgiving Jen's mother arrives, leading Dawson to confront her about her secret past. He tries to bring Jen and her mother closer. Gail is frustrated with Grams taking over cooking.

Name: Valentine's Day Massacre
Description: Joey questions Dawson's judgment when he and Pacey lead their friends to a secret party on a golf course hosted by a wealthy and snobbish student.

Name: Self Reliance
Description: Joey struggles to find time to study when Bessie goes on a weekend getaway, as she juggles responsibilities at the B&B and Pacey's advances. Dealing with her emotions about Dawson kissing Gretchen at the Christmas party.

Name: Four Scary Stories
Description: Joey, Jack, and Pacey share scary stories at Grams' house after watching a disappointing horror film. Joey recounts a spooky incident at the library on Halloween night while studying alone.

Name: Living Dead Girl
Description: Dawson sees a ghostly apparition and suspects Todd's up to something at his Halloween costume party. Meanwhile, Jack encourages Jen to call C.J., but when he shows up at the party with another guy, Jen thinks he's gay.

Name: Merry Mayhem
Description: Dawson returns to Capeside for Christmas. He struggles with his feelings about Natasha's relationship with Max, while Todd's drinking concerns Gail. Joey arrives with Audrey, and Eddie surprises them with a Christmas tree.

Name: The Prank King
Description: Dre worries that his family's Halloween tradition of playing outrageous pranks on each other will be ruined when his older children refuse to participate.

Name: Black Santa/White Christmas
Description: Dre wants to have a black Santa at his office Christmas party, despite HR already assigning the role. Meanwhile, Bow doesn't want to compete with Ruby for cooking the holiday dinner.

Name: Big Night, Big Fight
Description: Dre strives to maintain harmony on Valentine's Day while Diane's brothers and sisters endeavor to teach her the art of giving compliments.

Name: Jacked o' Lantern
Description: Dre's children are disappointed when their cousins come to the neighborhood to trick-or-treat; Dre also has to face his childhood bully, his cousin June Bug.

Name: Stuff
Description: Dre wants to reduce the commercialization of Christmas and spend more time together. His parents suggest cutting down on gifts but the kids don't agree.

Name: The Purge
Description: Dre teaches his son a lesson in pranking after being embarrassed during a basketball game. Meanwhile, the neighborhood participates in mischief night for Halloween, where petty crimes are allowed.

Name: Auntsgiving
Description: Pops' sister Almaviligerais shows up for Thanksgiving, much to everyone's delight except Ruby. While Bow and Dre go on vacation, the kids try to uncover why Ruby has a grudge against Almaviligerais.

Name: Just Christmas, Baby
Description: Dre aims to make a memorable Christmas for his family as Zoey prepares to leave for college. Meanwhile, Bow takes care of Gigi's newborn and realizes the challenges of motherhood.

Name: Scarred for Life
Description: The twins refuse to participate in the family Halloween costume, worrying it will ruin their social standing in school. To help them, Dre and Bow create a haunted house and invite their entire seventh-grade class.

Name: Christmas in Theater Eight
Description: The Johnson family struggles to agree on which movie to watch during their annual Christmas theater trip. Junior feels embarrassed when his ex mistakes him for a theater employee.

Name: Dreamgirls and Boys
Description: Dre and Bow deal with identity politics, Diane faces heartbreak as her crush starts spending time with another girl, and Junior's Valentine's Day date goes wrong after a talk about chivalry.

Name: Everybody Blames Raymond
Description: The Johnsons clash over the family Halloween costume and try to make Devante's first trick-or-treating experience perfect. They also try to get rid of Jack's new friend Raymond.

Name: Father Christmas
Description: Pops surprises Dre with holiday cheer, but a visitor from Lynette's past dampens the family's holiday spirit.

Name: The Gauntlet
Description: Dre struggles to find the perfect Valentine's Day gift for Bow, while Ruby's outdated dating advice fails to help Jack with his love problems.

Name: Compton Around the Christmas Tree
Description: Dre takes his family to his hometown of Compton to reconnect with his roots, but Bow has an idea to teach the kids about the spirit of giving by having them volunteer.

Name: Santa's Little Helper
Description: Cory tries to get Shawn a present after his dad gets laid off at Christmas. Morgan is traumatized when Santa Claus has a heart attack.

Name: Who's Afraid of Cory Wolf?
Description: Cory thinks he might be a werewolf after being bitten by an animal, and a fortune teller confirms it. She warns him of three prophecies, one involving killing a girl who loves him.

Name: Train of Fools
Description: The teens are stranded without transportation and end up spending New Year's Eve in an abandoned subway car.

Name: Turkey Day
Description: Cory and Shawn try to promote unity between their families by suggesting they celebrate Thanksgiving together after learning about tribal prejudices in Africa.

Name: Easy Street
Description: Cory gets a job at a Mafia-controlled restaurant but quits when he finds out. Shawn takes the job instead to earn money for Christmas.

Name: A Long Walk to Pittsburgh: Part 1
Description: Shawn kisses Topanga on the cheek and Eric tells Cory, causing tension. When Cory learns Topanga is moving away, he realizes his priorities.

Name: A Long Walk to Pittsburgh: Part 2
Description: Topanga runs away from home in the rain to convince her parents to let her live with an aunt in town. Cory and Topanga must prove their love to their parents.

Name: The Witches of Pennbrook
Description: Jack prioritizes his new girlfriend over his friendship with Eric, who uncovers that she's a witch. While Eric tries to warn Jack, Topanga conquers her fear of flying during a trip to Pittsburgh with Cory.

Name: Chasing Angela: Part 2
Description: Shawn confesses to Cory about his feelings for Angela after a mix-up with a lost purse, but is uncertain if Angela feels the same way. Meanwhile, Eric and Jack host Thanksgiving dinner for the Matthews family in their new apartment.

Name: A Very Topanga Christmas
Description: Cory invites Topanga to spend Christmas with his family, but they clash over their differing holiday traditions, causing Cory to question their future together.

Name: First Girlfriends' Club
Description: Shawn's ex-girlfriends kidnap him on Valentine's Day to prevent him from hurting Angela, convinced that he will ruin their relationship. Meanwhile, Topanga reads a letter from Lauren and Cory must face the consequences.

Name: Santa's Little Helpers
Description: Cory and Topanga confront the fact that Shawn and Angela still have feelings for each other, but they disagree on how to handle the situation.

Name: My Baby Valentine
Description: Cory plans a baby shower for Amy, but it turns out to be a disaster. Amy goes into premature labor, and the family rushes to the hospital. Meanwhile, Shawn is lost and Morgan is unhappy about the new baby. Jack and Rachel worry about Eric's reaction to their relationship.

Name: The First Thanksgiving
Description: Dharma tries to cook Thanksgiving dinner while Kitty makes a restaurant reservation as a backup plan.

Name: Haus Arrest
Description: Dharma struggles to take care of Greg's teenage cousin, Jennifer.

Name: Dharma and Greg's First Romantic Valentine's Day Weekend
Description: Greg's plan for a romantic weekend getaway goes awry, leaving him and his partner disappointed. Meanwhile, Kitty suspects that Larry may be interested in mate-swapping.

Name: See Dharma Run
Description: Dharma receives a parking ticket while feeding expired meters out of kindness, which leads her to run for the Board of Supervisors. Meanwhile, Jane and Pete tie the knot on Valentine's Day.

Name: The Very Grateful Dead
Description: Dharma channels the spirit of a deceased neighbor woman who lived an unfulfilled life, leading her to confront the regrets she has in her own life.

Name: Thanksgiving Until It Hurts
Description: Greg and Dharma struggle to balance Thanksgiving celebrations hosted by both their families. Abby has a breakdown over preparing the turkey, and Kitty's cooking is a disaster.

Name: The Trouble with Troubador
Description: Bob Dylan calls Dharma while Greg is in the middle of confirming their Valentine's weekend plans, surprising Greg that they were already friends from playing music together.

Name: Used Karma
Description: Dharma buys a haunted sports car previously owned by a gangster named Shorty Green. Meanwhile, Edward hires a security professional to catch the Halloween egg thrower at his house.

Name: Wish We Weren't Here
Description: Greg and Dharma's Thanksgiving Bahamas trip is cancelled due to bad weather, leaving them stranded in Fort Wayne. While Greg tries to rebook their flights, Dharma helps a couple save their relationship before their wedding.

Name: The Christmas Episode
Description: Stabler enlists Benson and the task force to find his missing son Eli, while Wheatley contemplates his future.

Name: Last Christmas
Description: A unit of police officers is closing down when they receive an offer from Robert Silas to surrender and cooperate. As they head to meet him, they discover they are not the only ones looking for him.

Name: Fucksgiving
Description: Piper reconciles with Alex and prepares for a visit from Larry on Thanksgiving. But when Piper is sent to solitary confinement for dancing with Alex, she confronts harsh realities and reevaluates her life choices.

Name: Can't Fix Crazy
Description: Red's kitchen plan fails, inmates stage a Christmas pageant, and Piper's safety is threatened, leading her to reassess her plans.

Name: You Also Have a Pizza
Description: The inmates get ready for a Valentine's Day party and love is in the air. Red makes an intriguing discovery and Larry approaches Piper to be his prison mole.

Name: The First Secret
Description: Before Alison's disappearance, her friends want to be invited to Noel's Halloween party, while Jenna competes with Ali for the title of Queen Bee. Aria uncovers a surprising truth about her father.

Name: This Is a Dark Ride
Description: The Halloween episode of Rosewood features the Rosewood Halloween Ghost Train transforming into a party with a killer vibe, topped off with a performance by Adam Lambert.

Name: How the 'A' Stole Christmas
Description: During Christmas, the liars plan to attend the Ice Ball but 'A' interferes with their plans.

Name: Secret Santa
Description: During the holidays, Lightman travels to Afghanistan to help rescue two captured marines, relying on an American expatriate as his sole source of intel.

Name: Vampire Weekend
Description: Castle and Beckett investigate the death of a man wearing fangs in a graveyard during Halloween.

Name: Secret Santa
Description: Castle and Beckett's first Christmas together is disrupted when a man dressed as Santa falls from the sky, leading them to investigate the case.

Name: Reality Star Struck
Description: Castle and Beckett investigate the murder of a rising star on a reality TV show, The Wives of Wall Street. Meanwhile, Castle's Valentine's Day gift to Beckett doesn't go as planned.

Name: Bad Santa
Description: Castle aids a mafia boss in investigating the death of a physician associated with the organization. Meanwhile, Esposito dines with Lanie and her folks.

Name: Perky's Visit
Description: During Thanksgiving, Julia and Suzanne's mother, Perky, comes to visit with her friend Bernice Clifton. However, the holiday turns sour when they discover that a client was killed after an altercation with their delivery man.

Name: New Year's Daze
Description: Charlene's New Year's Eve party takes an unexpected turn when her boyfriend escapes from prison and shows up at the party.

Name: I'll Be Home for Christmas
Description: During Christmas, Mary Jo tries to prove Santa Claus exists to her son. Charlene visits as Santa, and Suzanne sends a department store Santa, causing chaos that ends with Anthony's broken ankle and the theft of presents.

Name: The First Day of the Last Decade of the Entire Twentieth Century Part 1
Description: Charlene is due on New Year's Day and stands to win a new car if her baby is the first born of the new decade.

Name: The First Day of the Last Decade of the Entire Twentieth Century Part 2
Description: Charlene goes into labor, while the ladies learn about the life experiences of a 102-year-old black woman in the South.

Name: Charlene Buys a House
Description: Charlene buys a haunted house and hires Sugarbaker & Associates to decorate it, but insists on being treated like any other customer despite the supernatural occurrences.

Name: An Echolls Family Christmas
Description: Veronica investigates the disappearance of poker winnings, while Keith is hired by Lynn Echolls to find a stalker who is threatening her husband Aaron.

Name: One Angry Veronica
Description: Veronica serves on a jury, Keith aids the mayor in finding the police station thief, and a former acquaintance reappears. Meanwhile, one of Veronica's friends meets an unfortunate fate.

Name: Mars, Bars
Description: Veronica is released from jail, and her friends go on a Valentine's Day scavenger hunt. Meanwhile, Josh plans to flee the country after learning the truth about his father, and Lamb tracks down Steve at Mindy's house.

Name: Red Scare
Description: The murder of an architect in his newly bought old mansion leads to an investigation uncovering rumors of a haunted house, hidden treasure, and angry descendants of the original owner.

Name: Jolly Red Elf
Description: As CBI investigates a Santa's death, Patrick finds out that he's a suspect in the death of a cop killer who was set on fire while in police custody.

Name: Torn Between Two Hannahs
Description: Miley's cousin Luanne visits for Halloween and decides to dress up as Hannah Montana to reveal Miley's secret identity at a Hollywood party.

Name: Killing Me Softly With His Height
Description: Miley meets a short guy named Conner while Christmas shopping and agrees to a date, but is concerned about their height difference.
